<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>The SQL Atlas — A Structured Journey</title>
<script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:ital,opsz,wght,SOFT@0,9..144,300..900,0..100;1,9..144,300..900,0..100&family=Figtree:wght@300;400;500;600;700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/marked@12/marked.min.js"></script>
<style>
  :root {
    --ink: #0c1220;
    --ink-soft: #111827;
    --ink-line: #1c2540;
    --parchment: #f3e6cf;
    --parchment-dim: #d8c9ae;
    --amber: #e5a63b;
    --amber-hot: #f5c55e;
    --teal: #67c9c0;
    --rust: #d26a4d;
    --muted: #8591a8;
    --font-scale: 1;
  }

  * { -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; }

  html, body {
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--parchment);
    font-family: 'Figtree', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 0.005em;
    font-size: calc(16px * var(--font-scale));
  }

  body::before {
    content: "";
    position: fixed; inset: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 0;
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse 80% 60% at 50% 0%, rgba(229,166,59,0.06), transparent 60%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse 70% 70% at 90% 100%, rgba(103,201,192,0.05), transparent 60%),
      linear-gradient(rgba(255,255,255,0.015) 1px, transparent 1px) 0 0 / 100% 32px,
      linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.015) 1px, transparent 1px) 0 0 / 32px 100%;
  }

  .serif { font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-variation-settings: "opsz" 144, "SOFT" 60; }
  .mono  { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; }

  .headline {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 144, "SOFT" 100;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    line-height: 0.95;
  }

  .small-caps {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .rule {
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, var(--amber) 20%, var(--amber) 80%, transparent);
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .chip {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 4px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.66rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(229,166,59,0.35);
    color: var(--amber-hot);
    background: rgba(229,166,59,0.06);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .chip.teal { border-color: rgba(103,201,192,0.35); color: var(--teal); background: rgba(103,201,192,0.06); }
  .chip.rust { border-color: rgba(210,106,77,0.4); color: var(--rust); background: rgba(210,106,77,0.07); }
  .chip.muted { border-color: rgba(133,145,168,0.3); color: var(--muted); background: rgba(133,145,168,0.04); }

  @keyframes rise {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(14px); }
    to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }
  .reveal { animation: rise 620ms cubic-bezier(0.2, 0.8, 0.2, 1) both; }

  .marquee {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 144, "SOFT" 100;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-style: italic;
    color: rgba(243,230,207,0.22);
    font-size: 10vw;
    line-height: 0.9;
    white-space: nowrap;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  @keyframes scroll-x {
    from { transform: translateX(0); }
    to { transform: translateX(-50%); }
  }
  .marquee-inner {
    display: inline-block;
    padding-left: 100%;
    animation: scroll-x 50s linear infinite;
  }

  /* ============================================
     SIDEBAR  — sticky tree TOC mirror
     ============================================ */
  .side {
    position: sticky;
    top: 1.25rem;
    max-height: calc(100vh - 2.5rem);
    overflow-y: auto;
    padding-right: 6px;
  }
  .side-heading {
    color: var(--muted);
    padding: 0 10px;
    margin: 1rem 0 0.4rem;
  }
  .sidetree details { margin: 0; }
  .sidetree summary {
    list-style: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 5px 10px;
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    border-left: 2px solid transparent;
    transition: all 160ms ease;
  }
  /* hide ALL native markers — we use ::marker for a single custom arrow */
  .sidetree summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .sidetree summary { list-style: none; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0; }
  .sidetree summary::before {
    content: "▸";
    display: inline-block;
    width: 16px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    transition: transform 160ms ease, color 160ms ease;
  }
  .sidetree details[open] > summary::before { transform: rotate(90deg); color: var(--amber); }
  .sidetree summary:hover { color: var(--parchment); border-left-color: var(--amber); background: rgba(229,166,59,0.04); }
  .sidetree details[open] > summary { color: var(--amber-hot); }
  .sidetree details details summary { font-size: 0.68rem; padding-left: 12px; }
  .sidetree details details details summary { padding-left: 24px; font-size: 0.66rem; opacity: 0.9; }
  .sidetree a {
    display: block;
    padding: 3px 10px 3px 34px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.66rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    opacity: 0.85;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .sidetree a:hover { color: var(--amber); background: rgba(229,166,59,0.04); }
  .sidetree a.active { color: var(--amber); background: rgba(229,166,59,0.08); }
  .sidetree summary .side-nav-link {
    display: inline;
    padding: 0;
    color: inherit;
    background: none;
    opacity: 1;
    text-decoration: none;
    flex: 1;
    cursor: pointer;
  }
  .sidetree summary:hover .side-nav-link { color: var(--amber); }

  /* ============================================
     FACET FILTER bar
     ============================================ */
  .facets { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 6px; }
  .facet {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.66rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 3px 9px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    border: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
    color: var(--muted);
    background: transparent;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 160ms ease;
  }
  .facet:hover { color: var(--parchment); border-color: var(--amber); }
  .facet.active { background: var(--amber); color: var(--ink); border-color: var(--amber); font-weight: 700; }

  /* ============================================
     SEARCH input + ⌘K palette
     ============================================ */
  .search {
    background: rgba(12,18,32,0.6);
    border: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
    color: var(--parchment);
    padding: 9px 14px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    width: 100%;
    outline: none;
    transition: border-color 200ms ease;
  }
  .search:focus { border-color: var(--amber); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(229,166,59,0.08); }
  .search::placeholder { color: var(--muted); }

  .palette-backdrop {
    position: fixed; inset: 0;
    background: rgba(6,10,20,0.8);
    backdrop-filter: blur(6px);
    z-index: 90;
    display: none;
    align-items: flex-start;
    justify-content: center;
    padding-top: 12vh;
  }
  .palette-backdrop.open { display: flex; }
  .palette {
    width: min(640px, 92vw);
    background: var(--ink-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--amber);
    border-radius: 4px;
    box-shadow: 0 30px 80px rgba(0,0,0,0.6);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .palette input {
    width: 100%;
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--parchment);
    border: none;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 1rem;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    outline: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
  }
  .palette-list {
    max-height: 48vh;
    overflow-y: auto;
    padding: 6px 0;
  }
  .palette-item {
    padding: 8px 20px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--parchment-dim);
    display: flex;
    gap: 10px;
    align-items: center;
    cursor: pointer;
  }
  .palette-item .kind {
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--amber);
    width: 56px;
  }
  .palette-item.active, .palette-item:hover {
    background: rgba(229,166,59,0.1);
    color: var(--amber-hot);
  }

  /* ============================================
     PROGRESS RING
     ============================================ */
  .ring { transform: rotate(-90deg); }
  .ring-bg { stroke: var(--ink-line); }
  .ring-fg { stroke: var(--amber); stroke-linecap: round; transition: stroke-dashoffset 500ms ease; }

  /* Reading progress bar */
  .readbar {
    position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; height: 2px;
    background: linear-gradient(to right, var(--amber), var(--rust));
    z-index: 50; transition: width 120ms ease;
  }

  /* ============================================
     RESUME CARD
     ============================================ */
  .resume {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(229,166,59,0.07), rgba(229,166,59,0.02));
    border: 1px solid rgba(229,166,59,0.3);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--amber);
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 14px 18px;
    display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .resume-icon { font-size: 1.4rem; color: var(--amber); }
  .resume-body { flex: 1; }
  .resume-label { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.68rem; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--amber); }
  .resume-target { font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--parchment); margin-top: 2px; }

  /* ============================================
     GUIDE  — renders from embedded MD into a collapsible tree
     ============================================ */
  .guide { color: var(--parchment-dim); font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.75; }
  .guide p { margin: 0.9rem 0; max-width: 70ch; }

  .guide h1, .guide h2, .guide h3, .guide h4, .guide h5 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 144, "SOFT" 90;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.022em;
    color: var(--parchment);
    scroll-margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ========= Disclosure tree =========
     Three levels: .phase-node > .section-node > .subnode */
  .phase-node, .section-node, .subnode {
    position: relative;
    margin: 0;
  }
  /* Force-hide body when closed — Chrome's ::details-content is unreliable. */
  details:not([open]) > .phase-body,
  details:not([open]) > .section-body,
  details:not([open]) > .subnode-body,
  details:not([open]) > .guide-body,
  details:not([open]) > .guide-body-inline {
    display: none !important;
  }
  .phase-node {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
    padding: 0.4rem 0;
  }
  .phase-node:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink-line); }

  .phase-node > summary,
  .section-node > summary,
  .subnode > summary {
    list-style: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: grid;
    /* caret · title · star · meta-chips */
    grid-template-columns: 1.6rem 1fr auto auto;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    padding: 12px 0;
    transition: background 160ms ease;
  }
  .phase-node > summary::-webkit-details-marker,
  .section-node > summary::-webkit-details-marker,
  .subnode > summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }

  .phase-node > summary:hover,
  .section-node > summary:hover,
  .subnode > summary:hover { background: rgba(229,166,59,0.03); }

  .caret-tri {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 0; height: 0;
    border: 5px solid transparent;
    border-left-color: var(--muted);
    transition: transform 200ms ease;
    transform-origin: 3px 5px;
  }
  details[open] > summary .caret-tri { transform: rotate(90deg); border-left-color: var(--amber); }

  .phase-node > summary .phase-num {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 144, "SOFT" 100;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 2.6rem;
    line-height: 0.85;
    color: var(--amber);
    opacity: 0.9;
    min-width: 3rem;
    text-shadow: 0 0 28px rgba(229,166,59,0.3);
  }
  .phase-node > summary .phase-title {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 1.7rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--parchment);
  }
  .phase-node > summary .phase-sub {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Figtree', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.86rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-top: 2px;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .phase-body {
    padding: 0.6rem 0 1.8rem 3.4rem;
    border-left: 1px solid rgba(229,166,59,0.16);
    margin-left: 0.8rem;
  }

  /* Preamble (doc H1) — smaller, non-numbered, teal accent instead of amber */
  .phase-node.phase-preamble > summary {
    padding-top: 1rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }
  .phase-node.phase-preamble > summary .preamble-mark {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--teal);
    opacity: 0.7;
    min-width: 1.6rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .phase-node.phase-preamble > summary .phase-title {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--parchment);
    opacity: 0.92;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }
  .phase-node.phase-preamble > summary .phase-sub {
    font-size: 0.76rem;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    font-style: normal;
    color: var(--teal);
    opacity: 0.65;
  }
  .phase-node.phase-preamble > .phase-body {
    border-left-color: rgba(103, 201, 192, 0.22);
  }

  .section-node {
    border-top: 1px dashed rgba(28, 37, 64, 0.8);
  }
  .section-node:first-child { border-top: none; }
  .section-node > summary .sec-mark {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    color: var(--teal);
    font-size: 0.86rem;
    font-style: italic;
    opacity: 0.9;
    min-width: 3rem;
  }
  .section-node > summary .sec-title {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--parchment);
  }
  .section-node > summary .sec-sub {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-top: 1px;
  }

  .section-body {
    padding: 0.2rem 0 1rem 3rem;
    border-left: 1px solid rgba(103,201,192,0.12);
    margin-left: 0.4rem;
  }

  .subnode > summary .sub-glyph {
    color: var(--amber);
    opacity: 0.55;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    min-width: 1.6rem;
  }
  .subnode > summary .sub-title {
    font-family: 'Figtree', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    color: var(--parchment);
  }
  .subnode-body {
    padding: 0.3rem 0 0.8rem 2.2rem;
  }

  summary .meta {
    display: flex; gap: 5px; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: flex-end;
  }

  /* ------- Star button (per-section favourite) -------
     Rendered as an outlined ☆ glyph inside each phase/section/subnode summary.
     Clicking toggles `starred` state which is persisted under atlas.star.<id>.
     The summary's native toggle is suppressed on click so starring doesn't
     accidentally collapse/expand the node. */
  summary .star-btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 24px; height: 24px;
    margin-right: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1;
    cursor: pointer;
    color: var(--muted);
    opacity: 0.4;
    transition: color 180ms ease, opacity 180ms ease, transform 160ms ease,
                background 180ms ease;
    user-select: none;
    flex: 0 0 auto;
  }
  summary:hover .star-btn { opacity: 0.85; }
  summary .star-btn:hover {
    color: var(--amber);
    opacity: 1;
    transform: scale(1.18);
    background: rgba(229,166,59,0.07);
  }
  summary .star-btn.starred {
    color: var(--amber-hot);
    opacity: 1;
    text-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(229,166,59,0.45);
  }

  /* Starred-only facet: slight accent when active. */
  .facet[data-facet="starred"].active {
    background: var(--amber-hot);
    color: var(--ink);
    border-color: var(--amber-hot);
  }

  /* status dot */
  .status { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-right: 4px; }
  .status.todo { color: var(--muted); }
  .status.att  { color: var(--amber); }
  .status.pass { color: var(--teal); }

  /* difficulty chip colour map */
  .chip.diff-Easy   { border-color: rgba(103,201,192,0.45); color: var(--teal);  background: rgba(103,201,192,0.08); }
  .chip.diff-Medium { border-color: rgba(229,166,59,0.45);  color: var(--amber-hot); background: rgba(229,166,59,0.08); }
  .chip.diff-Hard   { border-color: rgba(210,106,77,0.5);   color: var(--rust);  background: rgba(210,106,77,0.1); }

  /* Inline MD styling inside guide bodies */
  .guide-body {
    padding-top: 0.4rem;
    animation: rise 260ms ease;
  }
  .guide-body p { margin: 0.8rem 0; max-width: 72ch; }
  .guide-body strong { color: var(--parchment); font-weight: 600; }
  .guide-body em { color: var(--parchment); font-style: italic; font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; }
  .guide-body h4 { font-size: 1rem; margin: 1.2rem 0 0.4rem; color: var(--teal); font-style: italic; }
  .guide-body h5 {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    font-size: 0.74rem;
    color: var(--amber);
    margin: 1rem 0 0.3rem;
  }
  .guide-body ul, .guide-body ol { margin: 0.6rem 0 1rem; padding-left: 1.2rem; max-width: 72ch; }
  .guide-body ul { list-style: none; }
  .guide-body ul > li { position: relative; padding-left: 1rem; margin: 0.25rem 0; }
  .guide-body ul > li::before {
    content: "◆";
    position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0;
    color: var(--amber);
    font-size: 0.58rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }
  .guide-body ol { list-style: none; counter-reset: ol; }
  .guide-body ol > li { counter-increment: ol; position: relative; padding-left: 1.7rem; margin: 0.25rem 0; }
  .guide-body ol > li::before {
    content: counter(ol);
    position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.76rem;
    color: var(--amber);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .guide-body hr {
    margin: 2rem 0; border: none; height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, var(--ink-line) 20%, var(--ink-line) 80%, transparent);
  }
  .guide-body code {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.84em;
    background: rgba(229,166,59,0.08);
    color: var(--amber-hot);
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(229,166,59,0.12);
  }
  .guide-body pre {
    position: relative;
    background: #060a14;
    border: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--amber);
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 14px 18px;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--parchment);
  }
  .guide-body pre code { background: transparent; border: none; color: inherit; padding: 0; font-size: inherit; }
  .guide-body pre .kw  { color: var(--amber-hot); font-weight: 700; }
  .guide-body pre .fn  { color: var(--teal); }
  .guide-body pre .com { color: var(--muted); font-style: italic; }
  .guide-body pre .str { color: #b8e5df; }
  .guide-body pre .num { color: var(--rust); }

  /* copy button on code blocks */
  .copy-btn {
    position: absolute; top: 6px; right: 6px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    background: rgba(12,18,32,0.8);
    border: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
    padding: 3px 8px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    cursor: pointer;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 160ms ease, color 160ms ease;
  }
  .guide-body pre:hover .copy-btn { opacity: 1; }
  .copy-btn:hover { color: var(--amber); border-color: var(--amber); }

  .guide-body blockquote {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding: 0.6rem 1.1rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--teal);
    background: rgba(103,201,192,0.05);
    color: var(--parchment);
    font-style: italic;
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }
  .guide-body table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1.1rem 0;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
  }
  .guide-body thead { background: rgba(229,166,59,0.06); }
  .guide-body th {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 9px 14px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--amber);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
  }
  .guide-body td {
    padding: 8px 14px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(28, 37, 64, 0.6);
    color: var(--parchment-dim);
    vertical-align: top;
  }
  .guide-body tr:hover td { background: rgba(229,166,59,0.03); }

  .guide-body a.practice-pill {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
    background: var(--amber);
    color: var(--ink) !important;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    text-decoration: none !important;
    transition: all 180ms ease;
  }
  .guide-body a.practice-pill:hover {
    background: var(--amber-hot);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 14px -4px rgba(229,166,59,0.5);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }
  /* per-pill status dot */
  .guide-body a.practice-pill .pill-dot {
    width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 50%; display: inline-block;
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgba(12,18,32,0.35) inset;
  }
  .pill-dot.todo { background: rgba(12,18,32,0.35); }
  .pill-dot.att  { background: #e5a63b; box-shadow: 0 0 6px rgba(229,166,59,0.7); }
  .pill-dot.pass { background: #67c9c0; box-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(103,201,192,0.8); }
  /* deep-link flash on ?jump=<slug> */
  @keyframes pillFlash {
    0%, 100% { box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 rgba(229,166,59,0); transform: none; }
    20%      { box-shadow: 0 0 0 6px rgba(229,166,59,0.4); transform: translateY(-1px); }
  }
  .guide-body a.practice-pill.pill-flash { animation: pillFlash 1.6s ease-out; }
  /* row accent — subtly tints the row of a solved problem */
  .guide-body tr[data-status="passed"] td { background: rgba(103,201,192,0.05); }
  .guide-body tr[data-status="attempted"] td { background: rgba(229,166,59,0.035); }
  .guide-body a.xref {
    color: var(--teal);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: rgba(103,201,192,0.35);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
  .guide-body a.xref:hover { color: var(--amber-hot); text-decoration-color: var(--amber); }

  /* =====================================================================
     QUIZ CARDS — inline theory / guess-the-output / scenario MCQs. Each
     block is a self-contained <div class="quiz"> authored directly in the
     markdown source; the JS renderer transforms it into a clickable widget
     with instant correct/wrong feedback and an explanation reveal. Progress
     persists under localStorage `atlas.quiz.<id>` so the user sees their
     previously chosen answer when they return.
     ===================================================================== */
  .guide-body .quiz {
    margin: 1.4rem 0;
    padding: 1rem 1.15rem 1.1rem;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(229,166,59,0.06), rgba(12,18,32,0.55));
    border: 1px solid rgba(229,166,59,0.28);
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgba(12,18,32,0.35) inset,
                0 8px 28px rgba(0,0,0,0.28);
    position: relative;
  }
  .guide-body .quiz::before {
    content: "❓";
    position: absolute;
    top: -12px; left: 14px;
    background: var(--ink);
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(229,166,59,0.35);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }
  .guide-body .quiz-kind {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--amber);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(229,166,59,0.4);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: rgba(229,166,59,0.08);
  }
  .guide-body .quiz-q {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--parchment);
    margin: 0.3rem 0 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  /* Embedded SQL / data blocks inside a quiz are more compact than prose <pre>. */
  .guide-body .quiz pre {
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0.8rem;
    padding: 0.6rem 0.8rem;
    background: rgba(12,18,32,0.6);
    border: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .guide-body .quiz .quiz-data-label {
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--parchment-dim);
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.2rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .guide-body .quiz-opts {
    list-style: none !important;
    padding: 0 !important;
    margin: 0 !important;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
  }
  .guide-body .quiz-opts li {
    margin: 0 !important;
    padding: 9px 40px 9px 34px;
    background: rgba(12,18,32,0.55);
    border: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
    border-radius: 6px;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--parchment);
    transition: border-color 120ms ease, background 120ms ease, transform 80ms ease;
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.45;
    user-select: none;
  }
  /* Letter badge (A/B/C/D) rendered via JS into data-letter. */
  .guide-body .quiz-opts li::before {
    content: attr(data-letter);
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    left: 10px;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    width: 18px; height: 18px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 1px solid rgba(229,166,59,0.45);
    color: var(--amber);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }
  .guide-body .quiz-opts li:hover:not(.is-locked) {
    border-color: rgba(229,166,59,0.55);
    background: rgba(229,166,59,0.08);
    transform: translateX(2px);
  }
  .guide-body .quiz-opts li.is-correct {
    border-color: var(--teal);
    background: rgba(103,201,192,0.12);
    color: var(--teal);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .guide-body .quiz-opts li.is-correct::after {
    content: "✓";
    position: absolute;
    right: 12px;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    color: var(--teal);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .guide-body .quiz-opts li.is-wrong {
    border-color: var(--rust);
    background: rgba(210,106,77,0.12);
    color: var(--rust);
  }
  .guide-body .quiz-opts li.is-wrong::after {
    content: "✕";
    position: absolute;
    right: 12px;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    color: var(--rust);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .guide-body .quiz-opts li.is-locked { cursor: default; }
  .guide-body .quiz-opts li.is-locked:not(.is-correct):not(.is-wrong) { opacity: 0.55; }
  .guide-body .quiz-why {
    display: none;
    margin-top: 0.9rem;
    padding: 0.75rem 0.9rem;
    background: rgba(103,201,192,0.08);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--teal);
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--parchment-dim);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .guide-body .quiz-why strong { color: var(--teal); }
  .guide-body .quiz-why code {
    background: rgba(12,18,32,0.7);
    padding: 1px 5px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-size: 0.85em;
  }
  .guide-body .quiz.is-answered .quiz-why { display: block; }
  .guide-body .quiz-footer {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    margin-top: 0.7rem;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--parchment-dim);
  }
  .guide-body .quiz-reset {
    background: none;
    border: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
    color: var(--parchment-dim);
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 120ms ease;
  }
  .guide-body .quiz-reset:hover { border-color: var(--amber); color: var(--amber); }

  /* dimmed for facet filter */
  .tree-dim > summary { opacity: 0.28; filter: grayscale(0.3); }

  /* scrollbars */
  ::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 8px; height: 8px; }
  ::-webkit-scrollbar-track { background: var(--ink); }
  ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: var(--ink-line); border-radius: 4px; }
  ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:hover { background: var(--amber); }

  /* print */
  @media print {
    .side, .readbar, .palette-backdrop, .marquee, .facets, .search-row, footer, .copy-btn { display: none !important; }
    details { page-break-inside: avoid; }
    details > * { display: block !important; }
  }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    * { animation-duration: 0.001ms !important; transition-duration: 0.001ms !important; }
  }

  footer {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
    margin-top: 5rem;
    padding: 3rem 0 4rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  /* =========================================================
     RESPONSIVE — tablet ≤1024px
     ========================================================= */
  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .guide-body { font-size: 0.95rem; }
    .guide-body pre { font-size: 0.8rem; padding: 0.9rem; }
    .guide-body table { font-size: 0.82rem; display: block; overflow-x: auto; -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch; }
    .guide-body th, .guide-body td { padding: 7px 10px; white-space: nowrap; }
    .facets { gap: 5px; }
    .facet { padding: 5px 10px; font-size: 0.72rem; }
    .search { font-size: 0.85rem; padding: 9px 12px; }
  }

  /* =========================================================
     RESPONSIVE — phone ≤768px
     Hide the persistent sidebar, stack hero + chips, shrink
     typography, make tables horizontally scrollable, collapse
     pacing-target rows to a stacked layout.
     ========================================================= */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    /* Prevent any intrinsic min-content child (pre, table, long word) from
       expanding the layout past the viewport — all nested scrolls stay local. */
    html, body { overflow-x: hidden !important; max-width: 100vw; }
    body { font-size: 15px; }
    header { padding-top: 4rem !important; padding-bottom: 1.5rem !important; }
    header > div { max-width: 100% !important; }
    .headline { font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 11vw, 3.5rem) !important; line-height: 1 !important; word-break: break-word; }
    header p { font-size: 1rem !important; }
    header .chip { font-size: 0.62rem; padding: 4px 9px; }

    /* Collapse the 240px side column — sidebar is already md:hidden.
       min-width:0 is critical: grid/flex items default to min-content sizing,
       and a single long table/pre/word inside would push the grid wider than
       the viewport. Clamping to 100vw plus min-width:0 forces children to
       shrink into local overflow-auto scrolls instead. */
    main {
      padding-left: 1rem !important;
      padding-right: 1rem !important;
      gap: 1rem !important;
      max-width: 100vw !important;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) !important;
      min-width: 0;
    }
    main > * { min-width: 0 !important; max-width: 100% !important; }
    main pre, main code { white-space: pre-wrap !important; word-break: break-word !important; }

    /* Search + facets stack */
    .search-row { flex-direction: column !important; align-items: stretch !important; }
    .facets { overflow-x: auto; flex-wrap: nowrap; -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch; padding-bottom: 4px; }
    .facets .facet { white-space: nowrap; }

    /* Pacing target card — stack each row vertically */
    .pacing-row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr !important;
      gap: 6px !important;
      text-align: left;
    }

    .guide-body { font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.65; }
    .guide-body h1 { font-size: 1.6rem; }
    .guide-body h2 { font-size: 1.3rem; }
    .guide-body h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; }
    .guide-body pre { font-size: 0.76rem; padding: 0.75rem; }
    .guide-body table { font-size: 0.8rem; }
    .guide-body th, .guide-body td { padding: 6px 8px; }
    .guide-body blockquote { font-size: 0.92rem; padding: 0.5rem 0.9rem; }

    .phase-head, .section-head, .subnode-head { padding: 10px 12px; gap: 8px; }
    .guide-body a.practice-pill { font-size: 0.62rem; padding: 4px 8px; letter-spacing: 0.1em; }

    /* Collapse the deep left-indent tree on mobile so content gets full width.
       Desktop: 3.4 + 3 + 2.2 = ~138px of dead space on a 390px screen.
       Mobile: give each level just enough (4-10px) to show the vertical rule. */
    .phase-body   { padding: 0.5rem 0 1.2rem 0.6rem !important; margin-left: 0.2rem !important; }
    .section-body { padding: 0.3rem 0 0.8rem 0.5rem !important; margin-left: 0.15rem !important; }
    .subnode-body { padding: 0.3rem 0 0.6rem 0.4rem !important; }

    /* Tree summaries — stack meta/chips below title to stop
       1-word-per-line wrapping of long phase titles on narrow screens. */
    .phase-node > summary,
    .section-node > summary,
    .subnode > summary {
      grid-template-columns: 1.2rem 1fr auto !important;
      gap: 8px !important;
    }
    /* Star pinned at top-right of the summary on mobile */
    .phase-node > summary > .star-btn,
    .section-node > summary > .star-btn,
    .subnode > summary > .star-btn {
      grid-column: 3;
      grid-row: 1;
    }
    .phase-node > summary > .meta,
    .section-node > summary > .meta,
    .subnode > summary > .meta {
      grid-column: 1 / span 3;
      margin-top: 4px;
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 4px;
    }
    .phase-node > summary .phase-num { font-size: 1.9rem !important; min-width: 2rem !important; }
    .phase-node > summary .phase-title { font-size: 1.25rem !important; }
    .phase-node > summary .phase-sub { font-size: 0.78rem; }

    /* Palette — full-screen on tiny viewports */
    .palette {
      width: calc(100vw - 28px);
      max-width: 100%;
      max-height: 70vh;
      top: 14px;
    }

    /* Resume card — stack */
    .resume { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 8px; padding: 12px 14px; }

    /* Hide decorative marquee on tiny screens (visual noise) */
    .marquee { display: none; }

    footer { margin-top: 3rem; padding: 2rem 0 3rem; }
  }

  /* =========================================================
     RESPONSIVE — tiny phone ≤420px
     ========================================================= */
  @media (max-width: 420px) {
    header { padding-top: 3rem !important; padding-bottom: 1rem !important; }
    .guide-body { font-size: 0.88rem; }
    .guide-body pre { font-size: 0.72rem; padding: 0.6rem; }
    .guide-body table { font-size: 0.74rem; }
    .guide-body th, .guide-body td { padding: 5px 7px; }
    .guide-body a.practice-pill { font-size: 0.58rem; padding: 3px 7px; }
    .phase-head, .section-head { font-size: 0.88rem; }
  }

  /* ============ VOYAGE MAP — captain sailing through phases ============ */
  .voyage-wrap {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    max-width: 56rem;
    animation: quoteFade 0.9s ease-out;
    animation-delay: 0.45s;
    animation-fill-mode: both;
  }
  /* ============ TREASURE-MAP VOYAGE ============ */
  .voyage-strip {
    position: relative;
    height: 180px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    /* aged parchment with warm browns and tan */
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 18% 30%, rgba(120,70,30,0.18) 0%, transparent 40%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 82% 72%, rgba(140,80,40,0.16) 0%, transparent 45%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 62% 18%, rgba(180,140,80,0.14) 0%, transparent 35%),
      radial-gradient(circle at 30% 65%, rgba(90,55,25,0.12) 0%, transparent 28%),
      linear-gradient(135deg, #e8d4a8 0%, #dec292 35%, #d1b27a 65%, #c4a36a 100%);
    border: 1px solid rgba(95, 55, 20, 0.45);
    box-shadow:
      inset 0 0 30px rgba(110, 65, 25, 0.22),
      inset 0 0 60px rgba(90, 50, 15, 0.18),
      0 3px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.35);
    overflow: hidden;
    padding: 0;
  }
  /* torn/burnt edge effect using overlayed gradients */
  .voyage-strip::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at top left,    rgba(60,30,10,0.35) 0%, transparent 18%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse at top right,   rgba(60,30,10,0.30) 0%, transparent 16%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse at bottom left, rgba(60,30,10,0.32) 0%, transparent 17%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse at bottom right,rgba(60,30,10,0.36) 0%, transparent 20%);
    pointer-events: none;
    mix-blend-mode: multiply;
  }
  /* subtle fiber/grain texture */
  .voyage-strip::after {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-image:
      repeating-linear-gradient(37deg,  rgba(80,45,15,0.04) 0 2px, transparent 2px 9px),
      repeating-linear-gradient(-42deg, rgba(80,45,15,0.035) 0 2px, transparent 2px 11px);
    pointer-events: none;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }
  /* SVG carries only the curved path (dashed route + travelled overlay).
     Ports + ship are DOM elements layered above — they stay true circles
     even when the SVG is stretched non-uniformly. */
  .voyage-map-svg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    overflow: visible;
    z-index: 1;
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  /* Per-item dash segments. One <use> per problem/MCQ in DOM order.
     JS sets stroke-dasharray + stroke-dashoffset on each so only the i-th
     slice of the full route shows through. Unsolved = rust-brown, solved =
     amber with a soft glow. */
  .voyage-seg {
    fill: none;
    stroke: #5a2f12;
    stroke-width: 2.4;
    stroke-linecap: round;
    opacity: 0.55;
    vector-effect: non-scaling-stroke;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 1px 0 rgba(255,240,200,0.2));
    transition: stroke 0.5s ease, stroke-width 0.5s ease,
                opacity 0.5s ease, filter 0.5s ease;
  }
  .voyage-seg.is-solved {
    stroke: #c85a1a;
    stroke-width: 3.4;
    opacity: 1;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 4px rgba(200, 90, 26, 0.65));
  }
  /* The segment the ship is currently parked on (first unsolved) — faint pulse
     so the captain can see exactly where they are without losing the dashes. */
  @keyframes voyageSegCurrent {
    0%, 100% { stroke: #8a4b1d; opacity: 0.75; }
    50%      { stroke: #c78038; opacity: 1;    }
  }
  .voyage-seg.is-current {
    animation: voyageSegCurrent 1.8s ease-in-out infinite;
    stroke-width: 2.8;
  }
  /* DOM-layer container that holds ports + ship (positioned by % over SVG) */
  .voyage-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    z-index: 2;
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  /* A single port marker (inked dot on parchment) */
  .voyage-port {
    position: absolute;
    width: 12px; height: 12px;
    margin-left: -6px; margin-top: -6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #f4e3b8;
    border: 1.8px solid #5a2f12;
    transition: background 0.4s, border-color 0.4s, transform 0.4s, box-shadow 0.4s;
    transform: translate(0,0);
  }
  .voyage-port.visited {
    background: #d67a1f;
    border-color: #7a3e10;
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(214, 122, 31, 0.7);
  }
  .voyage-port.current {
    transform: scale(1.35);
    box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(214, 122, 31, 0.9);
  }
  /* Port label (sits below/above its dot) */
  .voyage-port-label {
    position: absolute;
    font-family: 'Fraunces', 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 9px;
    font-style: italic;
    color: #4a2a0c;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    opacity: 0.82;
    pointer-events: none;
    white-space: nowrap;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
  }
  /* Fixed start/end markers (pinned to path endpoints) */
  .voyage-endpoint {
    position: absolute;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    pointer-events: none;
    text-align: center;
    line-height: 1;
  }
  .voyage-endpoint.start  { left: 5.5%;  top: 75%;  color: #5a2f12; font-size: 15px; }
  .voyage-endpoint.start::after  {
    content: "HARBOR";
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 8px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: #4a2a0c;
    margin-top: 4px;
    opacity: 0.82;
  }
  .voyage-endpoint.x-mark { left: 94.5%; top: 39%;  }
  .voyage-endpoint.x-mark .xmark-glyph {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 26px;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: #a63514;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 4px rgba(166, 53, 20, 0.5));
    animation: xMarkPulse 3.2s ease-in-out infinite;
    display: block;
  }
  .voyage-endpoint.x-mark.claimed .xmark-glyph {
    color: #d67a1f;
    animation: xMarkPulse 2s ease-in-out infinite, xMarkClaim 1.4s ease-out;
  }
  .voyage-endpoint.x-mark::after {
    content: "TREASURE";
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 8px;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    color: #a63514;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }
  @keyframes xMarkPulse {
    0%,100% { filter: drop-shadow(0 0 4px rgba(166, 53, 20, 0.5)); }
    50%     { filter: drop-shadow(0 0 14px rgba(214, 122, 31, 0.95)); }
  }
  @keyframes xMarkClaim {
    0%   { transform: scale(1); }
    40%  { transform: scale(1.4); }
    100% { transform: scale(1); }
  }
  /* Compass rose (top-right corner) */
  .voyage-compass {
    position: absolute;
    top: 10px;
    right: 12px;
    width: 44px;
    height: 44px;
    opacity: 0.78;
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 2;
    animation: compassSpin 60s linear infinite;
  }
  .voyage-compass .compass-ring { fill: none; stroke: #5a2f12; stroke-width: 1.5; opacity: 0.85; }
  .voyage-compass .compass-n    { fill: #a63514; }
  .voyage-compass .compass-arm  { fill: #5a2f12; }
  .voyage-compass .compass-letter { font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-size: 7px; fill: #4a2a0c; text-anchor: middle; font-weight: 700; }
  @keyframes compassSpin {
    from { transform: rotate(0); }
    to   { transform: rotate(360deg); }
  }
  /* Sea monster decoration — bottom-left flourish */
  .voyage-sea-flourish {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 8px;
    left: 12px;
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 10px;
    color: #5a2f12;
    opacity: 0.55;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 2;
  }
  /* The ship — DOM element layered over the SVG, rotated to follow the curve */
  .voyage-ship {
    position: absolute;
    left: 5%;
    top: 75%;
    width: 0; height: 0;
    transition: left 1.4s cubic-bezier(0.22, 0.61, 0.36, 1),
                top  1.4s cubic-bezier(0.22, 0.61, 0.36, 1);
    will-change: left, top;
    z-index: 3;
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .voyage-ship .ship-rotor {
    position: absolute;
    left: 0; top: 0;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%) rotate(0deg);
    transition: transform 1.4s cubic-bezier(0.22, 0.61, 0.36, 1);
    will-change: transform;
  }
  .voyage-ship .ship-icon {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 22px;
    line-height: 1;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 2px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.45));
    animation: shipBob 3.4s ease-in-out infinite;
  }
  .voyage-ship.arriving .ship-icon { animation: shipBob 3.4s ease-in-out infinite, shipArrive 1.4s ease-out; }
  @keyframes shipBob {
    0%,100% { transform: translateY(0); }
    50%     { transform: translateY(-3px); }
  }
  @keyframes shipArrive {
    0%   { filter: drop-shadow(0 0 0 rgba(214, 122, 31, 0)); }
    40%  { filter: drop-shadow(0 0 18px rgba(214, 122, 31, 0.95)); }
    100% { filter: drop-shadow(0 0 0 rgba(214, 122, 31, 0)); }
  }
  /* status line below the map */
  .voyage-log {
    margin-top: 0.55rem;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .voyage-log .log-tag { color: var(--amber); }
  .voyage-log .log-sep { margin: 0 0.6rem; color: rgba(232,180,94,0.3); }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .voyage-strip { height: 150px; }
    .voyage-port-label { font-size: 8px; }
    .voyage-ship-g .ship-icon { font-size: 18px; }
    .voyage-compass { width: 34px; height: 34px; top: 6px; right: 6px; }
  }

  /* ============ MOTIVATIONAL QUOTE BANNER (hero) ============ */
  .quote-banner {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding: 0.6rem 2rem 0.6rem 0.95rem;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--amber);
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(232,180,94,0.06), rgba(232,180,94,0.01) 70%, transparent);
    border-radius: 2px;
    max-width: 40rem;
    position: relative;
    animation: quoteFade 0.9s ease-out;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 0.55rem;
  }
  .quote-banner .quote-text {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', 'Figtree', serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: var(--parchment);
    letter-spacing: 0.003em;
    flex: 1 1 auto;
    min-width: 0;
  }
  .quote-banner .quote-text::before {
    content: "“";
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: var(--amber);
    margin-right: 0.15rem;
    vertical-align: -0.25rem;
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    opacity: 0.8;
  }
  .quote-banner .quote-text::after {
    content: "”";
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: var(--amber);
    margin-left: 0.1rem;
    vertical-align: -0.25rem;
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    opacity: 0.8;
  }
  .quote-banner .quote-author {
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .quote-banner .quote-author::before { content: "— "; color: var(--amber); opacity: 0.7; }
  .quote-banner .quote-reroll {
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    right: 0.45rem;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    width: 20px; height: 20px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 1px solid rgba(232,180,94,0.3);
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--amber);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    line-height: 18px;
    text-align: center;
    cursor: pointer;
    opacity: 0.55;
    transition: opacity 0.15s, transform 0.4s;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .quote-banner .quote-reroll:hover { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(-50%) rotate(180deg); }
  @keyframes quoteFade {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(4px); }
    to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .quote-banner { margin-top: 1.1rem; padding: 0.55rem 1.8rem 0.55rem 0.75rem; }
    .quote-banner .quote-text { font-size: 0.85rem; }
    .quote-banner .quote-author { font-size: 0.55rem; }
  }

  /* ============ CONQUEROR MODAL (all solved) ============ */
  .conqueror-scrim {
    position: fixed; inset: 0;
    background: radial-gradient(ellipse at center, rgba(22,28,40,0.88), rgba(8,10,15,0.96));
    backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
    z-index: 1000;
    display: none;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 2rem 1rem;
    animation: conqFade 0.6s ease-out;
  }
  .conqueror-scrim.open { display: flex; }
  .conqueror-card {
    max-width: 640px;
    width: 100%;
    padding: 3rem 2.5rem 2.2rem;
    background: linear-gradient(160deg, #1a2030 0%, #13171f 100%);
    border: 1px solid rgba(232,180,94,0.35);
    border-radius: 4px;
    box-shadow: 0 20px 80px -10px rgba(232,180,94,0.2), 0 0 0 1px rgba(232,180,94,0.05);
    position: relative;
    text-align: center;
    animation: conqRise 0.8s cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1);
  }
  .conqueror-card::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: -1px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, transparent 30%, rgba(232,180,94,0.5) 50%, transparent 70%);
    -webkit-mask: linear-gradient(#fff 0 0) content-box, linear-gradient(#fff 0 0);
    -webkit-mask-composite: xor;
            mask-composite: exclude;
    pointer-events: none;
    animation: conqShimmer 3.5s ease-in-out infinite;
  }
  .conqueror-crown {
    font-size: 2.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 12px rgba(232,180,94,0.5));
    animation: conqCrown 2.2s ease-in-out infinite;
  }
  .conqueror-title {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 2.2rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: var(--amber);
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .conqueror-sub {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.3em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .conqueror-quote {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--parchment);
    margin: 0 auto 1.4rem;
    max-width: 480px;
  }
  .conqueror-quote::before { content: "“"; color: var(--amber); font-size: 2rem; margin-right: 0.2rem; vertical-align: -0.3rem; }
  .conqueror-quote::after  { content: "”"; color: var(--amber); font-size: 2rem; margin-left: 0.1rem;  vertical-align: -0.3rem; }
  .conqueror-author {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal);
    margin-bottom: 2.2rem;
  }
  .conqueror-author::before { content: "— "; opacity: 0.7; }
  .conqueror-stats {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.8rem;
    padding: 1.1rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(232,180,94,0.15);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(232,180,94,0.15);
  }
  .conqueror-stat-val {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    color: var(--amber);
    line-height: 1;
  }
  .conqueror-stat-lbl {
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-top: 0.35rem;
  }
  .conqueror-btn {
    background: transparent;
    border: 1px solid var(--amber);
    color: var(--amber);
    padding: 0.65rem 1.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    border-radius: 2px;
    transition: background 0.2s, color 0.2s;
  }
  .conqueror-btn:hover { background: var(--amber); color: var(--ink); }
  .conqueror-close {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0.9rem; right: 1.1rem;
    width: 28px; height: 28px;
    background: transparent;
    border: 1px solid rgba(232,180,94,0.25);
    color: var(--muted);
    border-radius: 50%;
    cursor: pointer;
    line-height: 1;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }
  .conqueror-close:hover { color: var(--amber); border-color: var(--amber); }
  @keyframes conqFade { from { opacity: 0; } to { opacity: 1; } }
  @keyframes conqRise { from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(30px) scale(0.96); } to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0) scale(1); } }
  @keyframes conqShimmer { 0%,100% { opacity: 0.3; } 50% { opacity: 1; } }
  @keyframes conqCrown { 0%,100% { transform: translateY(0); } 50% { transform: translateY(-6px); } }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .conqueror-card { padding: 2rem 1.4rem 1.6rem; }
    .conqueror-title { font-size: 1.7rem; }
    .conqueror-quote { font-size: 1.05rem; }
    .conqueror-stats { gap: 1.5rem; }
    .conqueror-stat-val { font-size: 1.4rem; }
  }

  /* ============ UNIFIED VOYAGE MODAL — mode-based content visibility ============ */
  /* The modal is re-used for welcome / daily-streak / broken-streak / conqueror /
     manual — sections show or hide based on data-mode on the scrim. */
  #voyageScrim .voyage-card {
    max-width: 720px;
    padding: 2.2rem 2.2rem 1.8rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  /* Default: everything hidden except the map + quote */
  #voyageScrim .voyage-streak        { display: none; }
  #voyageScrim .conqueror-stats      { display: none; }
  #voyageScrim .voyage-name-capture  { display: none; }
  #voyageScrim .voyage-captain-log   { display: none; }

  /* Welcome — name input + quote + map, no streak, no stats. */
  #voyageScrim[data-mode="welcome"] .voyage-name-capture { display: block; }

  /* Daily (maintained or broken) — streak + quote + map */
  #voyageScrim[data-mode="daily-maintained"] .voyage-streak { display: block; }
  #voyageScrim[data-mode="daily-broken"]     .voyage-streak { display: block; }

  /* Conqueror — voyage log + stats + map */
  #voyageScrim[data-mode="conqueror"] .conqueror-stats    { display: flex; }
  #voyageScrim[data-mode="conqueror"] .voyage-captain-log { display: block; }

  /* Manual re-open — map only */
  #voyageScrim[data-mode="manual"] .voyage-streak  { display: none; }
  #voyageScrim[data-mode="manual"] .conqueror-stats { display: none; }

  /* Per-mode crown color accents */
  #voyageScrim[data-mode="daily-maintained"] .conqueror-crown { color: #e8b45e; }
  #voyageScrim[data-mode="daily-broken"]     .conqueror-crown { filter: drop-shadow(0 0 12px rgba(166, 53, 20, 0.5)); }
  #voyageScrim[data-mode="conqueror"]        .conqueror-crown { filter: drop-shadow(0 0 16px rgba(232, 180, 94, 0.7)); }

  /* Streak display */
  .voyage-streak {
    margin: 0 auto 1.4rem;
    padding: 1rem 1rem 0.9rem;
    max-width: 320px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(232, 180, 94, 0.2);
    border-radius: 6px;
    background: linear-gradient(160deg, rgba(232,180,94,0.05), transparent 70%);
    position: relative;
  }
  .voyage-streak .streak-glyph {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    animation: streakFlame 1.8s ease-in-out infinite;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 8px rgba(255, 140, 40, 0.45));
  }
  #voyageScrim[data-mode="daily-broken"] .voyage-streak .streak-glyph {
    animation: none;
    filter: grayscale(0.6) brightness(0.85);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }
  @keyframes streakFlame {
    0%,100% { transform: scale(1) rotate(-2deg); }
    50%     { transform: scale(1.08) rotate(2deg); }
  }
  .voyage-streak .streak-digits {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--amber);
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }
  #voyageScrim[data-mode="daily-broken"] .voyage-streak .streak-digits {
    color: #c9a572;
    opacity: 0.85;
  }
  .voyage-streak .streak-lbl {
    margin-top: 0.35rem;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.28em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .voyage-streak .streak-foot {
    margin-top: 0.55rem;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-style: italic;
    opacity: 0.88;
  }

  /* Captain-name capture (welcome mode) */
  .voyage-name-capture {
    margin: 0.2rem auto 1.6rem;
    max-width: 420px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .voyage-name-capture .name-label {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--parchment);
    margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
    opacity: 0.92;
  }
  .voyage-name-capture .name-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    padding: 0.55rem 0.8rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(232, 180, 94, 0.32);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: linear-gradient(160deg, rgba(232,180,94,0.08), rgba(232,180,94,0.02) 80%);
    transition: border-color 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
  }
  .voyage-name-capture .name-row:focus-within {
    border-color: var(--amber);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgba(232,180,94,0.25), 0 0 12px rgba(232,180,94,0.15);
  }
  .voyage-name-capture .name-prefix {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--amber);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    flex: 0 0 auto;
  }
  .voyage-name-capture .name-input {
    flex: 1 1 auto;
    background: transparent;
    border: none;
    outline: none;
    color: var(--parchment);
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-style: italic;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.1rem;
    min-width: 0;
  }
  .voyage-name-capture .name-input::placeholder {
    color: var(--muted);
    opacity: 0.6;
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .voyage-name-capture .name-hint {
    margin-top: 0.55rem;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    font-style: italic;
    opacity: 0.8;
  }
  .voyage-name-capture.is-error .name-row {
    border-color: #a63514;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgba(166, 53, 20, 0.35);
  }
  .voyage-name-capture.is-error .name-hint {
    color: #d67a1f;
    opacity: 1;
  }

  /* Voyage captain log (conqueror mode) — name + start/end dates + duration */
  .voyage-captain-log {
    margin: 0 auto 1.6rem;
    max-width: 520px;
    padding: 1.1rem 1.2rem 0.95rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(232,180,94,0.28);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: linear-gradient(160deg, rgba(232,180,94,0.06), transparent 80%);
    position: relative;
  }
  .voyage-captain-log::before,
  .voyage-captain-log::after {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    width: 40%;
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, rgba(232,180,94,0.45), transparent);
  }
  .voyage-captain-log::before { top: 0; }
  .voyage-captain-log::after  { bottom: 0; }
  .voyage-captain-log .log-row {
    text-align: center;
  }
  .voyage-captain-log .log-captain {
    margin-bottom: 0.95rem;
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', 'Fraunces', serif;
  }
  .voyage-captain-log .log-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.3em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-right: 0.7rem;
    vertical-align: 0.2rem;
  }
  .voyage-captain-log .log-value {
    font-size: 1.55rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--amber);
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }
  .voyage-captain-log .log-dates {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
  }
  .voyage-captain-log .log-date-block { min-width: 0; text-align: center; }
  .voyage-captain-log .log-date-lbl {
    font-size: 0.58rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.25em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  .voyage-captain-log .log-date-val {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--parchment);
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .voyage-captain-log .log-date-sep {
    color: rgba(232,180,94,0.45);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1;
  }
  .voyage-captain-log .log-duration {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal);
    opacity: 0.92;
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .voyage-captain-log .log-dates { gap: 0.7rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .voyage-captain-log .log-value { font-size: 1.25rem; }
  }

  /* Treasure map inside modal — slightly smaller, same look */
  .voyage-wrap-in-modal {
    margin: 0.4rem auto 1.3rem;
    max-width: 620px;
  }
  .voyage-wrap-in-modal .voyage-strip { height: 150px; }
  .voyage-wrap-in-modal .voyage-log   { font-size: 0.58rem; letter-spacing: 0.18em; margin-top: 0.4rem; }

  /* Modal quote — use conqueror-quote styling but smaller for welcome/daily */
  #voyageScrim .conqueror-quote {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
  }
  #voyageScrim[data-mode="conqueror"] .conqueror-quote {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
  }
  #voyageScrim .conqueror-author {
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }
  #voyageScrim[data-mode="conqueror"] .conqueror-author {
    margin-bottom: 2.2rem;
  }
  #voyageScrim .conqueror-sub {
    margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
  }

  /* Sidebar streak chip (always visible so users can track streak w/o popup) */
  .streak-chip {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.45rem;
    margin: 0.8rem 0.75rem 0;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.7rem;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(232,180,94,0.12), transparent);
    border: 1px solid rgba(232,180,94,0.18);
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--parchment);
  }
  .streak-chip .streak-chip-glyph {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 4px rgba(255, 140, 40, 0.4));
  }
  .streak-chip.cold .streak-chip-glyph { filter: grayscale(1); opacity: 0.5; }
  .streak-chip .streak-chip-val {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--amber);
    line-height: 1;
  }
  .streak-chip .streak-chip-lbl {
    font-size: 0.58rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  /* "Open voyage map" button in sidebar */
  .voyage-open-btn {
    width: 100%;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    #voyageScrim .voyage-card { padding: 1.6rem 1rem 1.2rem; }
    #voyageScrim .conqueror-title { font-size: 1.45rem; }
    #voyageScrim .conqueror-sub   { font-size: 0.6rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; }
    #voyageScrim .conqueror-quote { font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.5; }
    #voyageScrim[data-mode="conqueror"] .conqueror-quote { font-size: 1.05rem; }
    #voyageScrim .conqueror-crown { font-size: 2.1rem; margin-bottom: 0.2rem; }
    .voyage-streak { padding: 0.8rem 0.8rem 0.7rem; max-width: 260px; }
    .voyage-streak .streak-digits { font-size: 2.3rem; }
    .voyage-streak .streak-glyph  { font-size: 1.5rem; }
    .voyage-wrap-in-modal .voyage-strip { height: 130px; }
    .voyage-wrap-in-modal .voyage-compass { width: 32px; height: 32px; top: 5px; right: 5px; }
    .voyage-wrap-in-modal .voyage-sea-flourish { font-size: 8px; bottom: 4px; left: 6px; }
    .voyage-wrap-in-modal .voyage-port-label { font-size: 7.5px; }
    .voyage-wrap-in-modal .voyage-ship .ship-icon { font-size: 17px; }
    .voyage-wrap-in-modal { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    /* Name input stays readable on narrow screens */
    .voyage-name-capture { max-width: 100%; }
    .voyage-name-capture .name-label  { font-size: 0.9rem; }
    .voyage-name-capture .name-row    { padding: 0.45rem 0.6rem; gap: 0.4rem; }
    .voyage-name-capture .name-prefix { font-size: 0.95rem; }
    .voyage-name-capture .name-input  { font-size: 1rem; }
    .voyage-name-capture .name-hint   { font-size: 0.65rem; }
    /* Conqueror captain log — stack date blocks vertically if too narrow */
    .voyage-captain-log { padding: 0.9rem 0.9rem 0.75rem; }
    .voyage-captain-log .log-value { font-size: 1.2rem; }
    .voyage-captain-log .log-badge { display: block; margin: 0 0 0.25rem; }
    .voyage-captain-log .log-dates { gap: 0.6rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .voyage-captain-log .log-date-val { font-size: 0.85rem; }
    .voyage-captain-log .log-duration { font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.18em; }
  }

  /* ============ RESET CONFIRMATION MODAL ============ */
  .reset-scrim .reset-card {
    max-width: 560px;
    padding: 2rem 2rem 1.6rem;
    text-align: left;
    border: 1px solid rgba(166, 53, 20, 0.4);
    box-shadow: 0 20px 80px -10px rgba(166, 53, 20, 0.25), 0 0 0 1px rgba(166, 53, 20, 0.08);
  }
  .reset-scrim .reset-card::before {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, transparent 30%, rgba(166, 53, 20, 0.45) 50%, transparent 70%);
  }
  .reset-scrim .reset-icon {
    font-size: 2.2rem;
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 10px rgba(166, 53, 20, 0.45));
    animation: conqCrown 2.4s ease-in-out infinite;
  }
  .reset-scrim .reset-title {
    text-align: center;
    color: #d67a1f;
    font-size: 1.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }
  .reset-scrim .conqueror-sub {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
  }
  .reset-checklist {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(232, 180, 94, 0.12);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(232, 180, 94, 0.12);
  }
  .reset-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.6rem 0.2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px dashed rgba(232, 180, 94, 0.09);
  }
  .reset-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .reset-item .reset-ico {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
    flex: 0 0 1.8rem;
    text-align: center;
    opacity: 0.95;
  }
  .reset-item-body { flex: 1 1 auto; min-width: 0; }
  .reset-item-title {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--parchment);
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
  }
  .reset-item-sub {
    font-size: 0.74rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.4;
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .reset-item.is-preserved {
    opacity: 0.85;
  }
  .reset-item.is-preserved .reset-ico { opacity: 0.75; }
  .reset-item .reset-kept {
    color: var(--teal);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-left: 0.35rem;
  }
  .reset-warn {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #d67a1f;
    opacity: 0.9;
    margin: 1rem 0 1.3rem;
  }
  .reset-cta-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.8rem;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: stretch;
  }
  .reset-btn {
    flex: 1 1 auto;
    background: transparent;
    border: 1px solid rgba(232, 180, 94, 0.3);
    color: var(--parchment);
    padding: 0.65rem 1rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    border-radius: 2px;
    transition: background 0.2s, color 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;
    font-family: inherit;
  }
  .reset-btn-cancel:hover { background: rgba(232, 180, 94, 0.08); color: var(--amber); border-color: var(--amber); }
  .reset-btn-confirm {
    background: rgba(166, 53, 20, 0.1);
    color: #e08a3d;
    border-color: rgba(166, 53, 20, 0.5);
  }
  .reset-btn-confirm:hover {
    background: #a63514;
    color: #fff;
    border-color: #a63514;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .reset-scrim .reset-card { padding: 1.6rem 1.1rem 1.3rem; }
    .reset-scrim .reset-title { font-size: 1.5rem; }
    .reset-scrim .conqueror-sub { font-size: 0.58rem; }
    .reset-item { padding: 0.5rem 0.1rem; gap: 0.55rem; }
    .reset-item .reset-ico { flex-basis: 1.5rem; font-size: 1rem; }
    .reset-item-title { font-size: 0.82rem; }
    .reset-item-sub   { font-size: 0.68rem; }
    .reset-cta-row { flex-direction: column; }
    .reset-btn { width: 100%; }
    .reset-warn { font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.18em; margin: 0.8rem 0 1rem; }
  }

  /* ============ MOBILE VOYAGE FAB (floating action button) ============ */
  .voyage-fab {
    position: fixed;
    right: 16px;
    bottom: 18px;
    width: 56px;
    height: 56px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 1px solid rgba(232, 180, 94, 0.55);
    background: linear-gradient(160deg, #1f2634 0%, #141821 100%);
    color: var(--amber);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    cursor: pointer;
    z-index: 900;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 22px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.55), 0 0 0 1px rgba(232, 180, 94, 0.08);
    transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s, background 0.2s;
    -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;
  }
  .voyage-fab:active { transform: scale(0.94); }
  .voyage-fab .fab-glyph {
    display: block;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 2px 3px rgba(0,0,0,0.45));
  }
  .voyage-fab .fab-streak {
    position: absolute;
    top: -4px;
    right: -4px;
    min-width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    padding: 0 5px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: #a63514;
    color: #fff;
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    line-height: 20px;
    text-align: center;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(166, 53, 20, 0.6);
    border: 1.5px solid #141821;
  }
  .voyage-fab .fab-streak.cold { background: #52463a; box-shadow: none; }
  .voyage-fab.hidden-by-modal { display: none; }
  /* Extra safety: if a modal is open, hide the FAB so it doesn't overlap. */
  .conqueror-scrim.open ~ .voyage-fab { display: none; }
</style>
</head>

<body class="relative z-10">

<div class="readbar" id="readbar" style="width:0%"></div>

<!-- ================= HERO ================= -->
<header class="relative overflow-hidden pt-20 pb-10 md:pb-14">
  <div class="marquee absolute left-0 right-0 top-6 pointer-events-none select-none">
    <span class="marquee-inner">CTE · WINDOW · LAG · LEAD · GROUP&nbsp;BY · HAVING · ROW_NUMBER · RANK · DENSE_RANK · SELF&nbsp;JOIN · ANTI&nbsp;JOIN · PIVOT · SESSIONIZATION · GAPS&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;ISLANDS · CTE · WINDOW · LAG · LEAD · GROUP&nbsp;BY · HAVING · ROW_NUMBER · RANK · DENSE_RANK · SELF&nbsp;JOIN · ANTI&nbsp;JOIN · PIVOT · SESSIONIZATION · GAPS&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;ISLANDS&nbsp;·&nbsp;</span>
  </div>
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 relative">
    <h1 class="headline text-6xl md:text-8xl leading-[0.9] mb-8 reveal" style="animation-delay:.15s">
      The <em style="color:var(--amber);font-style:italic;">SQL</em> Atlas
    </h1>
    <p class="serif italic text-xl md:text-2xl max-w-2xl text-[color:var(--parchment-dim)] mb-10 reveal" style="animation-delay:.25s">
      A structured SQL interview prep guide — read the theory, then solve the problem right here in the browser. No account, no setup, progress saved locally.
    </p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 reveal" style="animation-delay:.35s">
      <span class="chip" title="Phase 0 – Phase 6 plus a Quick Reference: mental model, schema, core patterns, windows, advanced patterns, data types, performance.">7 Phases</span>
      <span class="chip teal" id="chipProblems" title="Every problem runs in an in-browser SQLite sandbox with a hidden edge-case validator.">58 Problems</span>
      <span class="chip" id="chipQuizzes" title="Multiple-choice quiz questions — guess-the-output and 'make-this-query-faster' scenarios. Progress tracked separately from problems.">0 Quizzes</span>
      <span class="chip rust" title="Your query is scored against a gold query across multiple datasets — not just the visible example. A pass means your query handles ties, NULLs, and empty groups.">Hidden Edge-Case Validator</span>
      <span class="chip muted" title="⌘K opens the jump palette · ?j / ?k move between sections · / focuses the filter.">⌘K to search · ?j for next section</span>
    </div>

    <div class="rule mt-10"></div>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- ================= UNIFIED VOYAGE MODAL =================
     Modes (set on #voyageScrim via data-mode):
       welcome           — first-ever landing
       daily-maintained  — once per day, streak intact
       daily-broken      — once per day, streak reset
       conqueror         — all problems + all MCQs done
       manual            — user clicked the sidebar "Voyage" button
============================================================= -->
<div class="conqueror-scrim" id="voyageScrim" data-mode="welcome"
     role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="voyageTitle" aria-hidden="true">
  <div class="conqueror-card voyage-card">
    <button class="conqueror-close" id="voyageClose" type="button" aria-label="Close">✕</button>
    <div class="conqueror-crown" id="voyageCrown">⚓</div>
    <div class="conqueror-title" id="voyageTitle">Welcome Aboard, Captain</div>
    <div class="conqueror-sub" id="voyageSub">Seven seas ahead · One wave at a time</div>

    <!-- CAPTAIN-NAME CAPTURE (welcome mode only) -->
    <div class="voyage-name-capture" id="voyageNameCapture">
      <label class="name-label" for="captainNameInput">What shall we call you, Captain?</label>
      <div class="name-row">
        <span class="name-prefix">Captain</span>
        <input class="name-input" id="captainNameInput" type="text"
               maxlength="32" autocomplete="off" spellcheck="false"
               placeholder="your name" />
      </div>
      <div class="name-hint" id="captainNameHint">The crew will need to know who's at the helm.</div>
    </div>

    <!-- STREAK (daily modes only) -->
    <div class="voyage-streak" id="voyageStreak">
      <div class="streak-glyph">🔥</div>
      <div class="streak-digits"><span id="streakNum">0</span></div>
      <div class="streak-lbl"><span id="streakLbl">Day Streak</span></div>
      <div class="streak-foot" id="streakFoot">Best: 0 · You've visited before, Captain.</div>
    </div>

    <!-- VOYAGE LOG (conqueror mode only) — captain's name + dates + duration -->
    <div class="voyage-captain-log" id="voyageCaptainLog">
      <div class="log-row log-captain">
        <span class="log-badge">Captain</span>
        <span class="log-value" id="conqCaptainName">—</span>
      </div>
      <div class="log-row log-dates">
        <div class="log-date-block">
          <div class="log-date-lbl">Set Sail</div>
          <div class="log-date-val" id="conqDateStart">—</div>
        </div>
        <div class="log-date-sep">◆</div>
        <div class="log-date-block">
          <div class="log-date-lbl">Treasure Claimed</div>
          <div class="log-date-val" id="conqDateEnd">—</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="log-duration" id="conqDuration">—</div>
    </div>

    <!-- QUOTE -->
    <div class="conqueror-quote" id="voyageQuote"></div>
    <div class="conqueror-author" id="voyageAuthor"></div>

    <!-- TREASURE MAP (embedded) -->
    <div class="voyage-wrap voyage-wrap-in-modal" aria-label="Voyage progress">
      <div class="voyage-strip" role="img" aria-label="Treasure map with ship sailing the seven seas">
        <svg class="voyage-compass" viewBox="0 0 44 44" aria-hidden="true">
          <circle class="compass-ring" cx="22" cy="22" r="19"/>
          <circle class="compass-ring" cx="22" cy="22" r="14"/>
          <polygon class="compass-n"   points="22,4 25,22 22,21 19,22"/>
          <polygon class="compass-arm" points="22,40 19,22 22,23 25,22"/>
          <polygon class="compass-arm" points="4,22 22,19 21,22 22,25"/>
          <polygon class="compass-arm" points="40,22 22,25 23,22 22,19"/>
          <text class="compass-letter" x="22" y="12">N</text>
        </svg>
        <div class="voyage-sea-flourish" aria-hidden="true">Here be the Seven Seas</div>

        <svg class="voyage-map-svg" id="voyageMapSvg"
             viewBox="0 0 1000 180" preserveAspectRatio="none"
             aria-hidden="true">
          <defs>
            <path id="treasureRoute"
                  d="M 55 135 C 145 85, 215 165, 300 110 S 440 55, 515 130 S 660 170, 755 85 S 880 35, 945 70" />
          </defs>
          <!-- Per-item dash segments are injected into this group at runtime.
               One <use> per problem/MCQ in DOM order — brown when unsolved,
               amber when solved. Generated by rebuildVoyageSegments(). -->
          <g id="voyageSegments"></g>
        </svg>

        <div class="voyage-overlay">
          <div class="voyage-endpoint start" aria-label="Harbor · departure">⚓</div>
          <div id="voyagePorts">
            <div class="voyage-port" data-phase="0"></div><div class="voyage-port-label" data-phase="0">MENTAL</div>
            <div class="voyage-port" data-phase="1"></div><div class="voyage-port-label" data-phase="1">SCHEMA</div>
            <div class="voyage-port" data-phase="2"></div><div class="voyage-port-label" data-phase="2">CORE</div>
            <div class="voyage-port" data-phase="3"></div><div class="voyage-port-label" data-phase="3">WINDOWS</div>
            <div class="voyage-port" data-phase="4"></div><div class="voyage-port-label" data-phase="4">ADVANCED</div>
            <div class="voyage-port" data-phase="5"></div><div class="voyage-port-label" data-phase="5">TYPES</div>
            <div class="voyage-port" data-phase="6"></div><div class="voyage-port-label" data-phase="6">PERF</div>
          </div>
          <div class="voyage-endpoint x-mark" id="voyageXMark" aria-label="Final port · treasure">
            <span class="xmark-glyph">✕</span>
          </div>
          <div class="voyage-ship" id="voyageShip" aria-live="polite">
            <div class="ship-rotor"><span class="ship-icon">⛵</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="voyage-log">
        <span class="log-tag">Captain's log</span>
        <span class="log-sep">·</span>
        <span id="voyageLog">Weighing anchor — departure harbor</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- STATS (conqueror mode only) -->
    <div class="conqueror-stats" id="voyageStats">
      <div>
        <div class="conqueror-stat-val" id="conqStatProblems">0</div>
        <div class="conqueror-stat-lbl">Problems</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="conqueror-stat-val" id="conqStatMcqs">0</div>
        <div class="conqueror-stat-lbl">MCQs</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="conqueror-stat-val">🏴‍☠️</div>
        <div class="conqueror-stat-lbl">Colours Raised</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <button class="conqueror-btn" id="voyageBtn" type="button">Set sail</button>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ================= RESET CONFIRMATION MODAL ================= -->
<div class="conqueror-scrim reset-scrim" id="resetScrim"
     role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="resetTitle" aria-hidden="true">
  <div class="conqueror-card reset-card">
    <button class="conqueror-close" id="resetCloseBtn" type="button" aria-label="Close">✕</button>
    <div class="reset-icon" aria-hidden="true">⚠️</div>
    <div class="conqueror-title reset-title" id="resetTitle">Scuttle the Ship?</div>
    <div class="conqueror-sub">This voyage will be reset — the ocean will forget you, Captain.</div>

    <ul class="reset-checklist" aria-label="Everything that will be cleared">
      <li class="reset-item">
        <span class="reset-ico" aria-hidden="true">🧭</span>
        <div class="reset-item-body">
          <div class="reset-item-title">Captain's name</div>
          <div class="reset-item-sub">You'll be prompted to name your captain again on the next sail.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="reset-item">
        <span class="reset-ico" aria-hidden="true">🏴‍☠️</span>
        <div class="reset-item-body">
          <div class="reset-item-title">Voyage dates &amp; conqueror status</div>
          <div class="reset-item-sub">Set-sail date, treasure-claimed date, and the <em>Captain of the Atlas</em> flag.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="reset-item">
        <span class="reset-ico" aria-hidden="true">🔥</span>
        <div class="reset-item-body">
          <div class="reset-item-title">Daily-visit streak</div>
          <div class="reset-item-sub">Current streak and your all-time best streak.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="reset-item">
        <span class="reset-ico" aria-hidden="true">✅</span>
        <div class="reset-item-body">
          <div class="reset-item-title">Every solved problem</div>
          <div class="reset-item-sub">All passed / attempted markers across the 58 practice problems.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="reset-item">
        <span class="reset-ico" aria-hidden="true">🎯</span>
        <div class="reset-item-body">
          <div class="reset-item-title">Every MCQ answer</div>
          <div class="reset-item-sub">All quiz picks and correctness records will be wiped.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="reset-item">
        <span class="reset-ico" aria-hidden="true">📍</span>
        <div class="reset-item-body">
          <div class="reset-item-title">Resume &amp; open-section state</div>
          <div class="reset-item-sub">Where you last were, which sections were expanded.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="reset-item is-preserved">
        <span class="reset-ico" aria-hidden="true">★</span>
        <div class="reset-item-body">
          <div class="reset-item-title">Starred sections <span class="reset-kept">— kept</span></div>
          <div class="reset-item-sub">Your favorite sections will <strong>stay starred</strong>.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <div class="reset-warn">This cannot be undone, Captain. The crew is watching.</div>

    <div class="reset-cta-row">
      <button class="reset-btn reset-btn-cancel" id="resetCancel" type="button">Belay that — keep sailing</button>
      <button class="reset-btn reset-btn-confirm" id="resetConfirm" type="button">Scuttle the ship</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Mobile floating action button — opens the voyage map when the sidebar
     button is hidden (md-below). -->
<button id="voyageFab" class="voyage-fab md:hidden" type="button"
        aria-label="Open voyage map">
  <span class="fab-glyph">⛵</span>
  <span class="fab-streak" id="fabStreak" aria-hidden="true">0</span>
</button>

<!-- ================= MAIN LAYOUT ================= -->
<main class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 pb-20 grid md:grid-cols-[240px_1fr] gap-10 relative">

  <!-- Sticky sidebar: tree TOC mirror -->
  <aside class="hidden md:block">
    <div class="side">
      <div class="small-caps side-heading">Progress</div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 px-3">
        <svg width="52" height="52" class="ring">
          <circle cx="26" cy="26" r="22" fill="none" stroke-width="3" class="ring-bg"></circle>
          <circle cx="26" cy="26" r="22" fill="none" stroke-width="3" class="ring-fg"
            stroke-dasharray="138.2" stroke-dashoffset="138.2" id="ringFg"></circle>
        </svg>
        <div>
          <div class="mono text-lg"><span id="progPct">0</span>%</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-[color:var(--muted)]"><span id="progCount">0</span> / <span id="progTotal">58</span> solved</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 px-3 mt-2 text-xs text-[color:var(--muted)]" title="Multiple-choice quiz questions answered correctly across the guide. Tracked separately from problems.">
        <span class="chip muted" id="quizProgChip">0 / 0 MCQ</span>
        <span>correct</span>
      </div>

      <div class="streak-chip" id="streakSidebarChip" title="Daily-visit streak. Come back tomorrow to extend it.">
        <span class="streak-chip-glyph">🔥</span>
        <span class="streak-chip-val" id="streakSidebarVal">0</span>
        <span class="streak-chip-lbl">Day Streak</span>
      </div>

      <div class="flex px-3 mt-3">
        <button id="openVoyage" class="facet voyage-open-btn" title="Open the voyage map">⛵ Voyage Map</button>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-2 px-3 mt-3">
        <button id="expandAll" class="facet">Expand</button>
        <button id="collapseAll" class="facet">Collapse</button>
        <button id="resetProg" class="facet">Reset</button>
      </div>

      <div class="small-caps side-heading mt-6">Contents</div>
      <nav id="sidetree" class="sidetree" role="tree"></nav>
    </div>
  </aside>

  <!-- Content column -->
  <section>
    <!-- Search + facets -->
    <div class="search-row flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-3 mb-5 reveal items-stretch md:items-center" style="animation-delay:.4s">
      <input id="search" class="search flex-1" placeholder="› Filter tree — or press ⌘K for jump palette" />
      <button id="paletteOpen" class="facet" style="padding:9px 14px">⌘K</button>
    </div>

    <div class="facets mb-3 reveal" style="animation-delay:.45s" id="facetBar">
      <button class="facet active" data-facet="all">All</button>
      <button class="facet" data-facet="starred" title="Show only sections you have starred">★ Starred</button>
      <button class="facet" data-facet="diff:Easy">Easy</button>
      <button class="facet" data-facet="diff:Medium">Medium</button>
      <button class="facet" data-facet="diff:Hard">Hard</button>
      <button class="facet" data-facet="status:todo">Not started</button>
      <button class="facet" data-facet="status:att">Attempted</button>
      <button class="facet" data-facet="status:pass">Passed</button>
    </div>

    <!-- Resume card slot -->
    <div id="resumeSlot"></div>

    <!-- THE GUIDE (tree) -->
    <article id="guide" class="guide" role="tree"></article>

    <!-- Interview pacing (kept as product surface) -->
    <section class="mt-16 reveal">
      <div class="small-caps text-[color:var(--rust)] mb-3">Interview Dossier</div>
      <h2 class="headline text-3xl md:text-4xl mb-6">Pacing Targets</h2>
      <div style="border:1px solid rgba(210,106,77,0.25); border-radius: 4px; background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(210,106,77,0.07), transparent);">
        <div class="pacing-row grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr_auto] gap-4 px-4 py-3 items-center" style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(210,106,77,0.12);">
          <span class="chip diff-Easy">Easy</span>
          <span class="serif text-lg">Read · Plan · Write · Verify</span>
          <span class="mono text-[color:var(--teal)] text-sm">≤ 10 min</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pacing-row grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr_auto] gap-4 px-4 py-3 items-center" style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(210,106,77,0.12);">
          <span class="chip diff-Medium">Medium</span>
          <span class="serif text-lg">Identify pattern · Decompose · CTE or Window · Verify</span>
          <span class="mono text-[color:var(--amber)] text-sm">≤ 20 min</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pacing-row grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr_auto] gap-4 px-4 py-3 items-center">
          <span class="chip diff-Hard">Hard</span>
          <span class="serif text-lg">Sketch approach · Handle edges · Multi-CTE or recursion</span>
          <span class="mono text-[color:var(--rust)] text-sm">≤ 30 min</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>
</main>

<!-- ⌘K palette -->
<div class="palette-backdrop" id="palette">
  <div class="palette" role="dialog" aria-label="Jump palette">
    <input id="paletteInput" placeholder="Type a phase, section, pattern, or problem…" autocomplete="off" />
    <div class="palette-list" id="paletteList"></div>
  </div>
</div>

<footer class="text-center">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="rule mb-10 opacity-40"></div>
    <p class="serif italic text-xl mb-3">&ldquo;A query is a compass. The schema is the terrain.&rdquo;</p>
    <p class="small-caps text-[color:var(--muted)]">Sandbox &middot; <span id="footerProblemCount">Fifty-eight</span> problems &middot; SQLite-WASM in your browser</p>
    <p class="mono text-[0.7rem] text-[color:var(--muted)] mt-6 uppercase tracking-widest">
      🌀 Compiled &amp; Cartographed locally &middot; No telemetry &middot; No server
    </p>
  </div>
</footer>

<script>
/* =====================================================================
   HELPERS
   ===================================================================== */
const $ = (sel, root = document) => root.querySelector(sel);
const $$ = (sel, root = document) => Array.from(root.querySelectorAll(sel));

function slugify(s) {
  return (s || "").toLowerCase()
    .replace(/[^\w\s-]/g, "")
    .trim()
    .replace(/\s+/g, "-")
    .replace(/-+/g, "-");
}

function highlightSQL(code) {
  const KW = /\b(SELECT|FROM|WHERE|GROUP|BY|HAVING|ORDER|LIMIT|OFFSET|JOIN|LEFT|RIGHT|FULL|INNER|OUTER|CROSS|LATERAL|ON|AS|AND|OR|NOT|IN|EXISTS|BETWEEN|LIKE|IS|NULL|CASE|WHEN|THEN|ELSE|END|WITH|RECURSIVE|UNION|ALL|INTERSECT|EXCEPT|DISTINCT|OVER|PARTITION|ROWS|RANGE|PRECEDING|FOLLOWING|CURRENT|ROW|UNBOUNDED|INSERT|UPDATE|DELETE|SET|VALUES|INTO|CREATE|TABLE|INDEX|DROP|ALTER|TRUNCATE|BEGIN|COMMIT|ROLLBACK|TRANSACTION|IF|DECLARE|RETURN|GRANT|REVOKE|VIEW|TRIGGER|PROCEDURE|FUNCTION|CAST|COALESCE|EXTRACT|INTERVAL|DATE|TIMESTAMP|BOOLEAN|INT|INTEGER|BIGINT|VARCHAR|TEXT|DECIMAL|NUMERIC|FLOAT|DOUBLE|ASC|DESC|NULLS|FIRST|LAST|USING|FILTER|WITHIN|GROUPING)\b/gi;
  const FN = /\b(COUNT|SUM|AVG|MIN|MAX|ROW_NUMBER|RANK|DENSE_RANK|NTILE|LAG|LEAD|FIRST_VALUE|LAST_VALUE|NTH_VALUE|CUME_DIST|PERCENT_RANK|NOW|CURDATE|CURRENT_DATE|CURRENT_TIMESTAMP|DATEDIFF|DATE_ADD|DATE_SUB|TIMESTAMPDIFF|STR_TO_DATE|DATE_FORMAT|TO_CHAR|TO_DATE|SUBSTRING|SUBSTR|LENGTH|CHAR_LENGTH|CONCAT|CONCAT_WS|UPPER|LOWER|TRIM|REPLACE|REGEXP_REPLACE|REGEXP_MATCH|ROUND|FLOOR|CEIL|CEILING|ABS|MOD|POWER|GROUP_CONCAT|STRING_AGG|ARRAY_AGG|JSON_EXTRACT|JSON_ARRAY|JSON_OBJECT|JSON_VALUE|IFNULL|NULLIF|GREATEST|LEAST|ISNULL|EXP|LN|LOG|SIGN|SQRT)\b/gi;
  return code
    .replace(/&/g, "&amp;").replace(/</g, "&lt;").replace(/>/g, "&gt;")
    .replace(/--[^\n]*/g, m => `<span class="com">${m}</span>`)
    .replace(/\/\*[\s\S]*?\*\//g, m => `<span class="com">${m}</span>`)
    .replace(/'[^']*'/g, m => `<span class="str">${m}</span>`)
    .replace(/\b\d+(?:\.\d+)?\b/g, m => `<span class="num">${m}</span>`)
    .replace(FN, m => `<span class="fn">${m}</span>`)
    .replace(KW, m => `<span class="kw">${m.toUpperCase()}</span>`);
}

/* =====================================================================
   STATUS + PROGRESS (localStorage bridge with sandbox)
   Keys:
     atlas.status.<slug> = "attempted" | "passed"
     atlas.fontScale     = number (font-size multiplier)
   ===================================================================== */
function getStatus(slug) {
  return localStorage.getItem(`atlas.status.${slug}`) || "todo";
}
function setStatus(slug, v) {
  localStorage.setItem(`atlas.status.${slug}`, v);
}

/* paint the small status dot inside each ▶ Practice pill */
function paintPillStatuses(root = document) {
  root.querySelectorAll(".pill-dot[data-dot-slug]").forEach(d => {
    const slug = d.dataset.dotSlug;
    const s = getStatus(slug);
    d.className = "pill-dot " + (s === "passed" ? "pass" : s === "attempted" ? "att" : "todo");
    d.setAttribute("aria-hidden", "true");
    // tooltip on the PARENT pill instead (so screen readers read it once)
    const pill = d.closest("a.practice-pill");
    if (pill) pill.setAttribute("aria-label", `${s === "passed" ? "Solved" : s === "attempted" ? "Attempted" : "Practice"}: ${slug}`);
  });
  // also mark each practice-pill's row for CSS purposes
  root.querySelectorAll("a.practice-pill").forEach(a => {
    const tr = a.closest("tr");
    if (!tr) return;
    tr.dataset.status = getStatus(a.dataset.slug);
  });
}

/* =====================================================================
   PATTERN DETECTION — inspects section heading text + body to tag chips
   ===================================================================== */
const PATTERN_RULES = [
  [/anti[- ]?join/i,      "Anti-Join"],
  [/semi[- ]?join/i,      "Semi-Join"],
  [/self[- ]?join/i,      "Self-Join"],
  [/recursive|recursion/i,"Recursive CTE"],
  [/window|row_number|rank\b|lag|lead|partition/i, "Window"],
  [/pivot|unpivot/i,      "Pivot"],
  [/gaps?\s*(and|&)?\s*islands?/i, "Gaps & Islands"],
  [/session(iz|is)/i,     "Sessionization"],
  [/year[- ]?over[- ]?year|yoy|month[- ]?over/i, "YoY"],
  [/subquery|CTE/i,       "CTE"],
  [/group\s*by|HAVING/i,  "Group-By"],
  [/null/i,               "NULL"],
  [/cast|conversion/i,    "Casting"],
  [/DATE|time/i,          "Date"],
  [/JSON|array/i,         "JSON/Array"],
  [/index|EXPLAIN|sarg/i, "Performance"],
  [/transaction|DML|procedure|view/i, "Server-Side"],
];
function detectPatterns(text) {
  const hits = new Set();
  for (const [re, label] of PATTERN_RULES) {
    if (re.test(text)) hits.add(label);
  }
  return [...hits];
}

/* =====================================================================
   PHASE BLURBS (one-line teasers)
   ===================================================================== */
const PHASE_BLURBS = {
  "Phase 0": "Logical order, NULLs, casting, CASE — the mental model SQL runs on.",
  "Phase 1": "Types, constraints, normalization, engine quirks — know the table before the query.",
  "Phase 2": "GROUP BY, CTEs, JOINs, Anti/Semi-joins — the standard-query toolbox.",
  "Phase 3": "RANK · LAG · LEAD · Frames — turn rows into analytics.",
  "Phase 4": "Gaps & Islands, Intervals, Recursion, Pivot, YoY — the hard tier.",
  "Phase 5": "Date, String, JSON, Array — fluent across every data type.",
  "Phase 6": "Indexes, EXPLAIN, Sargability, DML, Views — production-quality SQL.",
};

function phaseBlurb(title) {
  const m = title.match(/^Phase\s+(\d+)/i);
  if (m) return PHASE_BLURBS[`Phase ${m[1]}`] || "";
  return "";
}

/* =====================================================================
   TREE RENDERER — turn flat markdown DOM into nested <details>
   ===================================================================== */
function buildTree(root) {
  // Pull all direct children into an array
  const flat = [...root.children];
  root.innerHTML = "";

  // Group: iterate, collect by level
  let phaseNode = null, phaseBody = null;
  let sectionNode = null, sectionBody = null;
  let subNode = null, subBody = null;
  const all = [];

  function openPhase(h1) {
    phaseNode = document.createElement("details");
    phaseNode.className = "phase-node";
    phaseNode.dataset.level = "1";
    const sum = document.createElement("summary");
    const title = h1.textContent.trim();
    const m = title.match(/^Phase\s+(\d+)\s*[—–-]?\s*(.*)/i);
    const isPhase = !!m;
    const num = m ? m[1] : "";
    const rest = m ? m[2] : title;
    // any H1 that is NOT "Phase N — …" gets preamble treatment
    if (!isPhase) {
      phaseNode.classList.add("phase-preamble");
      // Preambles (How to read this Atlas, Quick Reference) stay collapsed
      // by default — users open them on demand like any other phase.
      sum.innerHTML = `
        <span class="caret-tri"></span>
        <span style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px;">
          <span class="preamble-mark">¶</span>
          <span>
            <span class="phase-title">${rest}</span>
            <span class="phase-sub">Doc preface · Legend · Navigation</span>
          </span>
        </span>
        <span class="star-btn" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-label="Star this section" title="Star this section">☆</span>
        <span class="meta"></span>
      `;
    } else {
      sum.innerHTML = `
        <span class="caret-tri"></span>
        <span style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:18px;">
          <span class="phase-num">${num}</span>
          <span>
            <span class="phase-title">${rest}</span>
            <span class="phase-sub">${phaseBlurb(title)}</span>
          </span>
        </span>
        <span class="star-btn" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-label="Star this section" title="Star this section">☆</span>
        <span class="meta"></span>
      `;
    }
    phaseNode.appendChild(sum);
    phaseBody = document.createElement("div");
    phaseBody.className = "phase-body";
    phaseNode.appendChild(phaseBody);
    phaseNode.id = slugify(title);
    phaseNode.dataset.title = title;
    root.appendChild(phaseNode);
    sectionNode = sectionBody = null;
    subNode = subBody = null;
    all.push(phaseNode);
  }

  function openSection(h2) {
    if (!phaseBody) {
      // orphan h2 (e.g. "How to Use This Guide"): give it a synthetic phase
      openPhase({ textContent: "Preface" });
    }
    sectionNode = document.createElement("details");
    sectionNode.className = "section-node";
    sectionNode.dataset.level = "2";
    const sum = document.createElement("summary");
    const title = h2.textContent.trim();
    const m = title.match(/^(\d+\.\d+)\s+(.*)$/);
    const mark = m ? `§${m[1]}` : "§";
    const rest = m ? m[2] : title;
    sum.innerHTML = `
      <span class="caret-tri"></span>
      <span style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px;">
        <span class="sec-mark">${mark}</span>
        <span>
          <span class="sec-title">${rest}</span>
          <span class="sec-sub"></span>
        </span>
      </span>
      <span class="star-btn" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-label="Star this section" title="Star this section">☆</span>
      <span class="meta"></span>
    `;
    sectionNode.appendChild(sum);
    sectionBody = document.createElement("div");
    sectionBody.className = "section-body";
    sectionNode.appendChild(sectionBody);
    sectionNode.id = slugify(title);
    sectionNode.dataset.title = title;
    phaseBody.appendChild(sectionNode);
    subNode = subBody = null;
    all.push(sectionNode);
  }

  function openSub(h3) {
    if (!sectionBody) {
      // orphan h3 → push into current phase (or synthetic section)
      if (!phaseBody) openPhase({ textContent: "Preface" });
      openSection({ textContent: "Details" });
    }
    subNode = document.createElement("details");
    subNode.className = "subnode";
    subNode.dataset.level = "3";
    const sum = document.createElement("summary");
    const title = h3.textContent.trim();
    sum.innerHTML = `
      <span class="caret-tri"></span>
      <span style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;">
        <span class="sub-glyph">▸</span>
        <span class="sub-title">${title}</span>
      </span>
      <span class="star-btn" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-label="Star this section" title="Star this section">☆</span>
      <span class="meta"></span>
    `;
    subNode.appendChild(sum);
    subBody = document.createElement("div");
    subBody.className = "subnode-body guide-body";
    subNode.appendChild(subBody);
    subNode.id = slugify(title);
    subNode.dataset.title = title;
    sectionBody.appendChild(subNode);
    all.push(subNode);
  }

  function appendBody(node) {
    // route to innermost open container
    if (subBody) { subBody.appendChild(node); return; }
    if (sectionBody) {
      // wrap in a guide-body if not already
      let gb = sectionBody.lastElementChild;
      if (!gb || !gb.classList?.contains("guide-body-inline")) {
        gb = document.createElement("div");
        gb.className = "guide-body guide-body-inline";
        sectionBody.appendChild(gb);
      }
      gb.appendChild(node);
      return;
    }
    if (phaseBody) {
      let gb = phaseBody.lastElementChild;
      if (!gb || !gb.classList?.contains("guide-body-inline")) {
        gb = document.createElement("div");
        gb.className = "guide-body guide-body-inline";
        phaseBody.appendChild(gb);
      }
      gb.appendChild(node);
      return;
    }
    // preamble before any phase: attach to root itself as a lead-in
    root.appendChild(node);
  }

  for (const el of flat) {
    const tag = el.tagName;
    if (tag === "H1") openPhase(el);
    else if (tag === "H2") openSection(el);
    else if (tag === "H3") openSub(el);
    else appendBody(el);
  }
  return all;
}

/* =====================================================================
   DECORATE: links, code highlight, copy buttons, meta chips per node
   ===================================================================== */
function decorate(root) {
  // links — only in-browser practice anymore
  root.querySelectorAll("a").forEach(a => {
    const href = a.getAttribute("href") || "";
    const txt = a.textContent.trim();
    if (href.startsWith("sql_sandbox.html?slug=")) {
      const slug = href.match(/slug=([a-z0-9-]+)/)?.[1];
      a.classList.add("practice-pill");
      a.setAttribute("target", "_blank");
      a.setAttribute("rel", "noopener");
      a.dataset.slug = slug || "";
      a.innerHTML = `<span class="pill-dot" data-dot-slug="${slug}"></span>▶ Practice`;
    } else if (href.startsWith("#")) {
      a.classList.add("xref");
    }
  });
  paintPillStatuses(root);

  // code highlight
  root.querySelectorAll("pre > code").forEach(c => {
    const lang = (c.className.match(/language-(\w+)/) || [])[1];
    if (!lang || /^sql$/i.test(lang)) {
      c.innerHTML = highlightSQL(c.textContent);
    }
    // copy button
    const pre = c.parentElement;
    if (pre && !pre.querySelector(".copy-btn")) {
      const btn = document.createElement("button");
      btn.className = "copy-btn";
      btn.textContent = "Copy";
      btn.addEventListener("click", async (e) => {
        e.stopPropagation();
        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(c.textContent);
        btn.textContent = "Copied";
        setTimeout(() => btn.textContent = "Copy", 1400);
      });
      pre.appendChild(btn);
    }
  });

  // quiz widgets — wire up click handlers, render option letters, restore state
  decorateQuizzes(root);
}

/* =====================================================================
   QUIZ WIDGETS — transforms authored <div class="quiz"> blocks into
   interactive MCQs. Authors write pure semantic HTML in the markdown:

     <div class="quiz" data-quiz-id="logical-order-1">
       <div class="quiz-kind">Theory</div>
       <div class="quiz-q">Question prose…</div>
       <ol class="quiz-opts">
         <li>Wrong answer</li>
         <li data-correct>Right answer</li>
       </ol>
       <div class="quiz-why">Explanation revealed after picking an option.</div>
     </div>

   The renderer adds A/B/C/D badges via data-letter, binds a click handler
   that locks the quiz on first pick, marks correct/wrong, reveals the
   explanation, and persists the choice under localStorage `atlas.quiz.<id>`.
   ===================================================================== */
const QUIZ_KEY = (id) => `atlas.quiz.${id}`;
function getQuizAnswer(id) {
  try { return JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem(QUIZ_KEY(id)) || "null"); }
  catch (_) { return null; }
}
function setQuizAnswer(id, payload) {
  try { localStorage.setItem(QUIZ_KEY(id), JSON.stringify(payload)); } catch (_) {}
}
function clearQuizAnswer(id) {
  try { localStorage.removeItem(QUIZ_KEY(id)); } catch (_) {}
}
function decorateQuizzes(root) {
  root.querySelectorAll(".quiz[data-quiz-id]").forEach(quiz => {
    if (quiz.dataset.quizWired === "1") return;
    quiz.dataset.quizWired = "1";

    const id = quiz.dataset.quizId;
    const opts = [...quiz.querySelectorAll(".quiz-opts > li")];
    // Stamp A/B/C/D letter badges (decorative, via CSS ::before content: attr).
    const LETTERS = "ABCDEFGH";
    opts.forEach((li, i) => { li.dataset.letter = LETTERS[i] || String(i+1); });

    // If the author didn't supply a footer, add a tiny reset control so a
    // user who mis-clicked can start over. Also a "pick to reveal" hint.
    if (!quiz.querySelector(".quiz-footer")) {
      const foot = document.createElement("div");
      foot.className = "quiz-footer";
      const hint = document.createElement("span");
      hint.className = "quiz-hint";
      hint.textContent = "Pick an option to reveal the explanation.";
      const reset = document.createElement("button");
      reset.type = "button";
      reset.className = "quiz-reset";
      reset.textContent = "Reset";
      foot.append(hint, reset);
      quiz.appendChild(foot);
    }

    function lockWithChoice(chosenIdx) {
      opts.forEach((li, i) => {
        const isCorrect = li.hasAttribute("data-correct");
        li.classList.add("is-locked");
        if (i === chosenIdx) {
          li.classList.add(isCorrect ? "is-correct" : "is-wrong");
        } else if (isCorrect) {
          // Also surface the right answer even if the user picked wrong.
          li.classList.add("is-correct");
        }
      });
      quiz.classList.add("is-answered");
      const hint = quiz.querySelector(".quiz-hint");
      if (hint) {
        const rightIdx = opts.findIndex(li => li.hasAttribute("data-correct"));
        const picked = opts[chosenIdx];
        const correct = picked && picked.hasAttribute("data-correct");
        hint.textContent = correct
          ? "✓ Correct — " + LETTERS[chosenIdx]
          : "✕ You picked " + LETTERS[chosenIdx] + " · correct answer is " + LETTERS[rightIdx];
      }
    }
    function resetQuiz() {
      opts.forEach(li => li.classList.remove("is-locked", "is-correct", "is-wrong"));
      quiz.classList.remove("is-answered");
      const hint = quiz.querySelector(".quiz-hint");
      if (hint) hint.textContent = "Pick an option to reveal the explanation.";
      clearQuizAnswer(id);
    }

    opts.forEach((li, i) => {
      li.addEventListener("click", () => {
        if (quiz.classList.contains("is-answered")) return;
        lockWithChoice(i);
        setQuizAnswer(id, { chosen: i, correct: li.hasAttribute("data-correct"), at: Date.now() });
        document.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent("atlas:quiz-answered", { detail: { id } }));
      });
    });
    const resetBtn = quiz.querySelector(".quiz-reset");
    if (resetBtn) resetBtn.addEventListener("click", () => {
      resetQuiz();
      document.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent("atlas:quiz-answered", { detail: { id, reset: true } }));
    });

    // Restore any previous answer so refresh doesn't erase progress.
    const prev = getQuizAnswer(id);
    if (prev && typeof prev.chosen === "number" && opts[prev.chosen]) {
      lockWithChoice(prev.chosen);
    }
  });
}

/* =====================================================================
   COMPUTE + PAINT meta chips (difficulty, pattern, count, status) on every summary
   ===================================================================== */
const NODE_INDEX = []; // { id, title, level, practiceSlugs[], patterns[], difficulty }

function computeAndPaintMeta(nodes) {
  for (const node of nodes) {
    const meta = node.querySelector(":scope > summary .meta");
    if (!meta) continue;
    const title = node.dataset.title || "";
    const level = parseInt(node.dataset.level || "0");
    const isPreamble = node.classList.contains("phase-preamble");
    const bodyText = node.textContent || "";

    // collect practice slugs underneath
    const practiceLinks = node.querySelectorAll("a.practice-pill");
    const practiceSlugs = [...practiceLinks].map(a => a.dataset.slug).filter(Boolean);
    const uniq = [...new Set(practiceSlugs)];

    // patterns — detect from title + prose, return top matches
    const patterns = detectPatterns(title + " " + bodyText.slice(0, 2000));

    // difficulty histogram — count ONLY rows that also carry a practice link,
    // and dedupe by slug so a problem listed in multiple practice tables
    // inside the same section (canonical-exemplar reuse) counts once.
    let easy = 0, med = 0, hard = 0;
    const seenSlugs = new Set();
    node.querySelectorAll("table tbody tr").forEach(tr => {
      const pill = tr.querySelector("a.practice-pill");
      if (!pill) return;
      const s = pill.dataset.slug;
      if (s && seenSlugs.has(s)) return;
      if (s) seenSlugs.add(s);
      for (const td of tr.querySelectorAll("td")) {
        const t = td.textContent.trim();
        if (t === "Easy") { easy++; break; }
        else if (t === "Medium") { med++; break; }
        else if (t === "Hard") { hard++; break; }
      }
    });
    const total = easy + med + hard;

    // sample-problem leaf: if title starts with "📝 Sample Problem"
    const isProblem = /Sample Problem/i.test(title);
    const slug = node.dataset.practiceSlug
      || (isProblem ? (node.querySelector("a.practice-pill")?.dataset.slug) : null);

    // status — for leaf problems, pull from localStorage
    let statusHtml = "";
    if (slug) {
      const s = getStatus(slug);
      const cls = s === "passed" ? "pass" : (s === "attempted" ? "att" : "todo");
      const glyph = s === "passed" ? "●" : (s === "attempted" ? "◐" : "○");
      statusHtml = `<span class="status ${cls}" title="${s}">${glyph}</span>`;
      node.dataset.practiceSlug = slug;
    }

    // per-node aggregate: "X/Y ▶"
    let solvedHtml = "";
    if (uniq.length > 0 && !slug) {
      const solved = uniq.filter(s => getStatus(s) === "passed").length;
      solvedHtml = `<span class="chip muted">${solved}/${uniq.length} ▶</span>`;
    }

    // separate quiz aggregate: "X/Y ?" — counted independently from problems
    let quizHtml = "";
    if (!slug) {
      const quizzes = node.querySelectorAll(".quiz[data-quiz-id]");
      if (quizzes.length > 0) {
        let qDone = 0, qCorrect = 0;
        quizzes.forEach(q => {
          const ans = getQuizAnswer(q.dataset.quizId);
          if (ans) { qDone++; if (ans.correct) qCorrect++; }
        });
        const qCls = qDone === 0 ? "muted"
                   : qCorrect === quizzes.length ? "teal" : "";
        quizHtml = `<span class="chip ${qCls}" data-quiz-chip="1" title="Multiple-choice quizzes answered correctly in this section">${qCorrect}/${quizzes.length} MCQ</span>`;
      }
    }

    // difficulty chip logic:
    //  • leaf problem: single chip of its own difficulty
    //  • section/phase WITH a practice table: show histogram "12M · 5H"
    //  • prose-only node: no chip (narrative mentions "Hard" shouldn't leak)
    let diffHtml = "";
    let dominantDiff = "";
    if (slug && total) {
      dominantDiff = hard ? "Hard" : med ? "Medium" : "Easy";
      diffHtml = `<span class="chip diff-${dominantDiff}">${dominantDiff}</span>`;
    } else if (total >= 2) {
      const parts = [];
      if (easy) parts.push(`<span class="chip diff-Easy">${easy}E</span>`);
      if (med) parts.push(`<span class="chip diff-Medium">${med}M</span>`);
      if (hard) parts.push(`<span class="chip diff-Hard">${hard}H</span>`);
      diffHtml = parts.join("");
      dominantDiff = hard >= med && hard >= easy ? "Hard" : med >= easy ? "Medium" : "Easy";
    } else if (total === 1) {
      dominantDiff = hard ? "Hard" : med ? "Medium" : "Easy";
      diffHtml = `<span class="chip diff-${dominantDiff}">${dominantDiff}</span>`;
    }

    // pattern chips: leaf → 1, section → up to 2, phase → up to 2
    const maxPats = level === 1 ? 2 : level === 2 ? 2 : 1;
    const patChipsHtml = patterns.slice(0, maxPats)
      .map(p => `<span class="chip teal">${p}</span>`).join("");

    // preamble phases (doc intro) get no chips at all
    if (isPreamble) {
      meta.innerHTML = "";
    } else {
      meta.innerHTML = statusHtml + diffHtml + patChipsHtml + solvedHtml + quizHtml;
    }

    // dataset tags for filter
    node.dataset.difficulty = dominantDiff || "";
    const diffSet = [];
    if (easy) diffSet.push("Easy");
    if (med)  diffSet.push("Medium");
    if (hard) diffSet.push("Hard");
    if (slug && !diffSet.length && dominantDiff) diffSet.push(dominantDiff);
    node.dataset.difficulties = diffSet.join("|"); // ← used by facet filter
    node.dataset.patterns = patterns.join("|");
    node.dataset.status = slug ? getStatus(slug) : "";
    node.dataset.practiceCount = uniq.length;

    NODE_INDEX.push({
      id: node.id,
      title,
      level: parseInt(node.dataset.level || "0"),
      patterns,
      difficulty: dominantDiff,
      slug,
      practiceCount: uniq.length,
    });

    // also stamp section-sub blurb: problem count + est reading time
    const secSub = node.querySelector(":scope > summary .sec-sub, :scope > summary .phase-sub");
    if (secSub && node.dataset.level !== "1") {
      const wc = (bodyText.match(/\b\w+\b/g) || []).length;
      const mins = Math.max(1, Math.round(wc / 220));
      const bits = [];
      if (uniq.length) bits.push(`${uniq.length} problem${uniq.length > 1 ? "s" : ""}`);
      bits.push(`${mins}m read`);
      secSub.textContent = bits.join(" · ");
    }
  }
}

/* =====================================================================
   SIDEBAR TREE (mirror of document tree)
   ===================================================================== */
function buildSidebar() {
  const side = $("#sidetree");
  side.innerHTML = "";
  const phases = $$("#guide > .phase-node");

  function makeSummary(title, targetId) {
    const s = document.createElement("summary");
    // ::before pseudo handles the single caret arrow via CSS
    s.innerHTML = `<a class="side-nav-link" data-target="${targetId}" href="#${targetId}">${title}</a>`;
    return s;
  }

  for (const ph of phases) {
    const d = document.createElement("details");
    d.appendChild(makeSummary(ph.dataset.title, ph.id));

    const sections = $$(":scope > .phase-body > .section-node", ph);
    for (const sec of sections) {
      const d2 = document.createElement("details");
      d2.appendChild(makeSummary(sec.dataset.title, sec.id));

      const subs = $$(":scope > .section-body > .subnode", sec);
      for (const sub of subs) {
        const a = document.createElement("a");
        a.href = `#${sub.id}`;
        a.textContent = sub.dataset.title;
        a.dataset.target = sub.id;
        d2.appendChild(a);
      }
      d.appendChild(d2);
    }
    side.appendChild(d);
  }

  side.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
    const a = e.target.closest("a[data-target]");
    if (!a) return;
    e.preventDefault();
    openTo(a.dataset.target);
  });
}

function openTo(idOrSlug) {
  // Try as section id first, then fall back to resolving as a practice slug
  let el = document.getElementById(idOrSlug);
  let highlightPill = null;
  if (!el) {
    highlightPill = document.querySelector(`a.practice-pill[data-slug="${idOrSlug}"]`);
    if (highlightPill) el = highlightPill.closest("tr") || highlightPill.closest(".subnode, .section-node, .phase-node");
  }
  if (!el) return;
  // open all ancestor <details>
  let cur = el;
  while (cur) {
    if (cur.tagName === "DETAILS") cur.open = true;
    cur = cur.parentElement;
  }
  el.scrollIntoView({ behavior: "smooth", block: "start" });
  if (highlightPill) {
    highlightPill.classList.add("pill-flash");
    setTimeout(() => highlightPill.classList.remove("pill-flash"), 1800);
  }
  if (history.replaceState && el.id) history.replaceState(null, "", "#" + el.id);
  // Remember this destination as the auto-resume target for next page load.
  if (el.id && el.matches && el.matches(".phase-node, .section-node, .subnode")) {
    try { localStorage.setItem("atlas.lastSection", el.id); } catch (_) {}
  }
}

/* =====================================================================
   STAR / FAVOURITE (per-section)
   ===================================================================== */
// localStorage schema:  atlas.star.<nodeId> = "1"   (presence = starred)
// We paint per-node on render and on every toggle so the whole cascade
// (tree summary + sidebar if mirrored later) stays in sync.
function isStarred(id) {
  try { return !!localStorage.getItem("atlas.star." + id); } catch (_) { return false; }
}
function setStarred(id, on) {
  try {
    if (on) localStorage.setItem("atlas.star." + id, "1");
    else    localStorage.removeItem("atlas.star." + id);
  } catch (_) {}
}
function paintStars(root) {
  (root || document).querySelectorAll(".phase-node, .section-node, .subnode").forEach(node => {
    const btn = node.querySelector(":scope > summary .star-btn");
    if (!btn) return;
    const on = isStarred(node.id);
    btn.classList.toggle("starred", on);
    btn.textContent = on ? "★" : "☆";
    // Also tag the node so the starred-facet filter can key off a fast
    // dataset lookup instead of hitting localStorage per node per re-filter.
    if (on) node.dataset.starred = "1";
    else    delete node.dataset.starred;
  });
}

/* =====================================================================
   FACET FILTER (dim, don't hide)
   ===================================================================== */
let activeFacet = "all";
function applyFacet(facet) {
  activeFacet = facet;
  $$(".facet").forEach(b => b.classList.toggle("active", b.dataset.facet === facet));
  const nodes = $$("#guide details");
  for (const n of nodes) {
    let keep = true;
    if (facet !== "all") {
      const [kind, val] = facet.split(":");
      if (kind === "diff") {
        // keep node if ANY problem beneath it carries that difficulty
        const diffs = (n.dataset.difficulties || "").split("|").filter(Boolean);
        keep = diffs.length ? diffs.includes(val) : false;
      }
      else if (kind === "status") {
        const s = n.dataset.status;
        if (val === "todo") keep = !s || s === "todo";
        else if (val === "att") keep = s === "attempted";
        else if (val === "pass") keep = s === "passed";
      }
      else if (facet === "starred") {
        // Keep a node if it is itself starred OR any descendant is starred
        // (so starring a subnode also keeps its ancestor section visible
        // as context instead of dimming the whole branch).
        const selfStarred = n.dataset.starred === "1";
        const descendantStarred = !!n.querySelector(":scope [data-starred='1']");
        keep = selfStarred || descendantStarred;
      }
    }
    n.classList.toggle("tree-dim", !keep);
  }
}

/* =====================================================================
   SEARCH (live, dim non-matching)
   ===================================================================== */
let searchTimer;
function applySearch(q) {
  q = (q || "").trim().toLowerCase();
  const nodes = $$("#guide details");
  for (const n of nodes) {
    const text = (n.dataset.title + " " + (n.dataset.patterns || "")).toLowerCase();
    const hit = !q || text.includes(q);
    n.classList.toggle("tree-dim", !hit);
    if (hit && q) n.open = true;
  }
}

/* =====================================================================
   ⌘K  PALETTE
   ===================================================================== */
function openPalette() {
  $("#palette").classList.add("open");
  $("#paletteInput").value = "";
  renderPalette("");
  setTimeout(() => $("#paletteInput").focus(), 10);
}
function closePalette() { $("#palette").classList.remove("open"); }

function renderPalette(q) {
  q = q.toLowerCase().trim();
  const list = $("#paletteList");
  const hits = NODE_INDEX
    .filter(n => !q || n.title.toLowerCase().includes(q) || (n.patterns || []).some(p => p.toLowerCase().includes(q)))
    .slice(0, 30);
  list.innerHTML = hits.map((h, i) => {
    const kind = h.level === 1 ? "Phase" : h.level === 2 ? "Section" : "Topic";
    return `<div class="palette-item ${i === 0 ? "active" : ""}" data-id="${h.id}">
      <span class="kind">${kind}</span>
      <span>${h.title}</span>
    </div>`;
  }).join("") || `<div class="palette-item"><span style="color:var(--muted)">no matches</span></div>`;
  list.querySelectorAll(".palette-item").forEach(el => {
    el.addEventListener("mouseenter", () => {
      list.querySelectorAll(".palette-item").forEach(x => x.classList.remove("active"));
      el.classList.add("active");
    });
    el.addEventListener("click", () => {
      const id = el.dataset.id;
      if (id) { closePalette(); openTo(id); }
    });
  });
}

/* =====================================================================
   RESUME card — shows last attempted node
   ===================================================================== */
function paintResume() {
  const slot = $("#resumeSlot");
  if (!slot) return;
  slot.innerHTML = "";
  const last = localStorage.getItem("atlas.lastSlug");
  if (!last) return;
  // Locate the pill that links to this slug (source of truth for resolution)
  const pill = document.querySelector(`a.practice-pill[data-slug="${last}"]`);
  if (!pill) return;
  const status = getStatus(last);
  if (status === "passed") return; // nothing to resume — already solved
  // Build a breadcrumb: Phase › Section › Subnode (or problem name from the row)
  const ph  = pill.closest(".phase-node");
  const sec = pill.closest(".section-node");
  const sub = pill.closest(".subnode");
  const row = pill.closest("tr");
  const problemName = row?.querySelectorAll("td")?.[1]?.textContent?.trim() || last;
  const crumb = [ph?.dataset.title, sec?.dataset.title, sub?.dataset.title, problemName]
    .filter(Boolean).join(" › ");
  const statusLabel = status === "attempted" ? "Resume · in progress" : "Resume where you left off";
  slot.innerHTML = `
    <div class="resume">
      <div class="resume-icon">⟲</div>
      <div class="resume-body">
        <div class="resume-label">${statusLabel}</div>
        <div class="resume-target">${crumb}</div>
      </div>
      <a href="sql_sandbox.html?slug=${last}" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
         class="facet active" style="padding:7px 14px">Jump</a>
    </div>
  `;
}

/* =====================================================================
   PROGRESS RING
   ===================================================================== */
function updateProgress() {
  // Source of truth = every practice-pill rendered in the atlas. NODE_INDEX
  // only tracks heading leaves (Sample Problem sections), so it undercounts
  // practice-table rows. Scan the live DOM for unique slugs instead.
  const pillSlugs = new Set();
  document.querySelectorAll("a.practice-pill").forEach(a => {
    if (a.dataset.slug) pillSlugs.add(a.dataset.slug);
  });
  // Fall back to NODE_INDEX-derived slugs if practice pills haven't rendered yet.
  const nodeSlugs = NODE_INDEX.filter(n => n.slug).map(n => n.slug);
  const uniq = [...new Set(pillSlugs.size ? pillSlugs : nodeSlugs)];
  const solved = uniq.filter(s => getStatus(s) === "passed").length;
  const total = uniq.length || 1;
  const pct = Math.round((solved / total) * 100);
  $("#progPct").textContent = pct;
  $("#progCount").textContent = solved;
  $("#progTotal").textContent = total;
  const ring = $("#ringFg");
  const circ = 2 * Math.PI * 22;
  ring.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", circ * (1 - solved / total));

  // Keep the landing-page "N Problems" chip and footer in sync with
  // the real, unique, discoverable problem count.
  const chip = document.getElementById("chipProblems");
  if (chip) chip.textContent = `${uniq.length} Problems`;
  const footer = document.getElementById("footerProblemCount");
  if (footer) footer.textContent = String(uniq.length);

  // --- SEPARATE quiz progress (NOT merged into the problem ring) -------
  const quizEls = document.querySelectorAll(".quiz[data-quiz-id]");
  let qTotal = 0, qCorrect = 0;
  quizEls.forEach(q => {
    qTotal++;
    const ans = getQuizAnswer(q.dataset.quizId);
    if (ans && ans.correct) qCorrect++;
  });
  const quizChip = document.getElementById("quizProgChip");
  if (quizChip) {
    quizChip.textContent = `${qCorrect} / ${qTotal} MCQ`;
    quizChip.classList.remove("teal", "muted");
    if (qTotal > 0 && qCorrect === qTotal) quizChip.classList.add("teal");
    else if (qCorrect === 0) quizChip.classList.add("muted");
  }
  const landingQuiz = document.getElementById("chipQuizzes");
  if (landingQuiz) landingQuiz.textContent = `${qTotal} Quizzes`;

  // --- VOYAGE MAP -----------------------------------------------------
  // Walk the atlas in DOM order and build the combined to-do list of every
  // unique practice problem + every MCQ, tagged with which Phase (0..6) it
  // belongs to. Items outside any "Phase N" container (preambles, quick
  // ref) get phase = -1 and don't count toward voyage progress.
  //
  // Port semantics:
  //   • You "arrive at port i" the moment every item in Phase i is solved.
  //   • Ship position between port i and port i+1 = fraction of Phase i+1
  //     that's solved.
  //   • Treasure is claimed when all seven phases are fully cleared.
  function _phaseIndex(el) {
    const ph = el.closest('.phase-node');
    if (!ph) return -1;
    const m = (ph.dataset.title || '').match(/^Phase\s+(\d+)/i);
    return m ? parseInt(m[1], 10) : -1;
  }
  const orderedItems = [];
  const seenSlugs = new Set();
  document.querySelectorAll(
    'a.practice-pill[data-slug], .quiz[data-quiz-id]'
  ).forEach(el => {
    const phase = _phaseIndex(el);
    if (el.matches('a.practice-pill')) {
      const slug = el.dataset.slug;
      if (!slug || seenSlugs.has(slug)) return;   // dedupe repeated pills
      seenSlugs.add(slug);
      orderedItems.push({
        type: 'problem', key: slug, phase,
        solved: getStatus(slug) === 'passed'
      });
    } else {
      const qid = el.dataset.quizId;
      if (!qid) return;
      const ans = getQuizAnswer(qid);
      orderedItems.push({
        type: 'quiz', key: qid, phase,
        solved: !!(ans && ans.correct)
      });
    }
  });

  // Bucket by phase (0..6) so we can compute per-phase completion.
  const phaseBuckets = [[], [], [], [], [], [], []];
  orderedItems.forEach(it => {
    if (it.phase >= 0 && it.phase <= 6) phaseBuckets[it.phase].push(it);
  });

  // Current phase = the first phase that still has any unsolved item.
  // If none — treasure claimed, currentPhase = 7 (sentinel).
  let currentPhase = 7;
  for (let p = 0; p < 7; p++) {
    const b = phaseBuckets[p];
    if (b.length && b.some(it => !it.solved)) { currentPhase = p; break; }
  }

  // Fraction of the current phase that's already done (0..1).
  let localProgress = 0;
  if (currentPhase < 7) {
    const b = phaseBuckets[currentPhase];
    if (b.length) {
      localProgress = b.filter(it => it.solved).length / b.length;
    }
  } else {
    localProgress = 1;
  }

  // Ship position along the route (0..1):
  //   harbor=0, MENTAL=1/8, SCHEMA=2/8, ..., PERF=7/8, TREASURE=1.
  // Each phase's leg of the route is 1/8 wide; within the leg we interpolate
  // by `localProgress`.
  const voyageFrac = currentPhase >= 7
    ? 1
    : (currentPhase + localProgress) / 8;

  // First-unsolved index (for the pulsing dash under the ship).
  const firstUnsolvedIdx = orderedItems.findIndex(it => !it.solved);

  // Cache so the voyage modal can re-paint without re-running this pipeline.
  _lastProgress = {
    total: uniq.length, solved, qTotal, qCorrect,
    frac: voyageFrac,
    currentPhase, localProgress,
    orderedTotal: orderedItems.length,
    firstUnsolved: firstUnsolvedIdx,
    ordered: orderedItems,               // full flat list (may include preambles)
    phaseBuckets                         // cached per-phase groupings
  };
  // Phase-aligned dash segments — each phase's items distributed evenly
  // inside that phase's 1/8 leg of the route. Keeps amber dashes visually
  // synced with the ship (which is also phase-aligned).
  rebuildVoyageSegments(phaseBuckets);
  paintVoyageSegments(phaseBuckets, currentPhase);
  updateVoyage(voyageFrac, currentPhase, localProgress, solved, uniq.length);
  // Keep the sidebar streak chip fresh (storage can change from other tabs).
  paintSidebarStreak();

  // Mastery check — fires the conqueror modal on the first paint where
  // every problem is passed AND every MCQ answered correctly.
  checkConqueror(uniq.length, solved, qTotal, qCorrect);
}

/* =====================================================================
   VOYAGE MAP — positions the ship along the horizon based on progress
   and lights up ports as they are reached.
   ===================================================================== */
const PHASE_LABELS = [
  { short: "Mental Model",        long: "Phase 0 — The Mental Model" },
  { short: "Schema",              long: "Phase 1 — Schema & Data Modeling" },
  { short: "Core Query Patterns", long: "Phase 2 — Core Query Patterns" },
  { short: "Windows",             long: "Phase 3 — Window Functions & Aggregation" },
  { short: "Advanced Patterns",   long: "Phase 4 — Advanced Patterns" },
  { short: "Data Types",          long: "Phase 5 — Data Type Manipulation" },
  { short: "Performance",         long: "Phase 6 — Performance & DML" },
];

let _voyageLastPhase = -1;
let _voyagePortsPlaced = false;
let _voyageSegCount = 0;   // current number of dash segments rendered

// SVG viewBox dimensions — must match the <svg viewBox="0 0 1000 180">.
// Points from getPointAtLength come back in this coordinate space, which we
// then convert to container percentages (the SVG stretches to fill).
const _VB_W = 1000, _VB_H = 180;

/* Rebuild the dash segments along the treasure route, grouped by phase.
   Each phase owns exactly 1/8 of the path (its "leg" between two ports).
   Inside a phase's leg we lay out ONE dash per problem/MCQ, evenly spaced.
   That way:
     • the total count of amber dashes = total solved items (still accurate),
     • and their POSITIONS stay aligned with the ship — whose position is
       also phase-aligned — so solving items in Phase 0 fills the Harbor→
       MENTAL leg, Phase 1 fills MENTAL→SCHEMA, etc.
   Preamble/orphan items (phase = -1) don't get dashes — they're not part
   of the voyage.
   Takes the array of 7 phase buckets [items...] (same order as phases 0..6).
*/
function rebuildVoyageSegments(phaseBuckets) {
  const svg  = document.getElementById("voyageMapSvg");
  const path = document.getElementById("treasureRoute");
  const g    = document.getElementById("voyageSegments");
  if (!svg || !path || !g) return;

  // Cache key — count per phase. If identical, skip the rebuild.
  const sig = (phaseBuckets || []).map(b => b.length).join(",");
  if (g.dataset.segSig === sig) return;
  g.innerHTML = "";
  g.dataset.segSig = sig;

  if (!phaseBuckets || !phaseBuckets.length) { _voyageSegCount = 0; return; }
  const totalLen = path.getTotalLength();
  if (!totalLen) { _voyageSegCount = 0; return; }

  const legLen = totalLen / 8;             // each phase owns 1/8 of the path
  const NS     = "http://www.w3.org/2000/svg";
  let count    = 0;

  for (let p = 0; p < 7; p++) {
    const bucket = phaseBuckets[p];
    const K = bucket ? bucket.length : 0;
    if (!K) continue;
    const slotLen  = legLen / K;
    const gap      = Math.max(1, slotLen * 0.22);     // 22% gap
    const dashSize = Math.max(0.5, slotLen - gap);
    for (let k = 0; k < K; k++) {
      const item = bucket[k];
      const slotStart = p * legLen + k * slotLen;
      const use = document.createElementNS(NS, "use");
      use.setAttributeNS("http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink", "href", "#treasureRoute");
      use.setAttribute("href", "#treasureRoute");
      use.setAttribute("class", "voyage-seg");
      use.setAttribute("data-phase", String(p));
      use.setAttribute("data-key", item.key);
      use.setAttribute("stroke-dasharray", `${dashSize} ${totalLen}`);
      use.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", String(-slotStart));
      g.appendChild(use);
      count++;
    }
  }
  _voyageSegCount = count;
}

/* Repaint each dash's state:
     • is-solved → amber (problem passed / MCQ correct)
     • is-current → faint pulse on the FIRST unsolved dash in the FIRST
                    still-active phase (where the ship is parked)
     • else      → brown (unsolved) */
function paintVoyageSegments(phaseBuckets, currentPhase) {
  const segs = document.querySelectorAll("#voyageSegments .voyage-seg");
  if (!segs.length || !phaseBuckets) return;
  // Find the key of the first unsolved item in the current phase, if any.
  let currentKey = null;
  if (currentPhase >= 0 && currentPhase < 7) {
    const bucket = phaseBuckets[currentPhase] || [];
    const hit = bucket.find(it => !it.solved);
    if (hit) currentKey = hit.key;
  }
  // Build a quick lookup from key → item for O(1) paint.
  const lookup = Object.create(null);
  for (const bucket of phaseBuckets) {
    if (!bucket) continue;
    for (const it of bucket) lookup[it.key] = it;
  }
  segs.forEach(el => {
    const key = el.getAttribute("data-key");
    const it  = lookup[key];
    el.classList.toggle("is-solved",  !!(it && it.solved));
    el.classList.toggle("is-current", key === currentKey);
  });
}

/* Place the 7 phase ports + labels at percentage positions along the curve. */
function placeVoyagePorts() {
  const path = document.getElementById("treasureRoute");
  if (!path || _voyagePortsPlaced) return;
  const totalLen = path.getTotalLength();
  if (!totalLen) return;
  const ports  = document.querySelectorAll('#voyagePorts .voyage-port');
  const labels = document.querySelectorAll('#voyagePorts .voyage-port-label');
  ports.forEach((port, i) => {
    const frac = (i + 1) / 8;
    const pt = path.getPointAtLength(totalLen * frac);
    const xPct = (pt.x / _VB_W) * 100;
    const yPct = (pt.y / _VB_H) * 100;
    port.style.left = xPct + "%";
    port.style.top  = yPct + "%";
    const lbl = labels[i];
    if (lbl) {
      const below = pt.y < _VB_H / 2;
      // Label above the port on top half of curve, below on bottom half,
      // offset by ~14% of strip height so it's readable.
      const labelYPct = below ? yPct - 10 : yPct + 11;
      lbl.style.left = xPct + "%";
      lbl.style.top  = labelYPct + "%";
    }
  });
  _voyagePortsPlaced = true;
}

/* Ship position is phase-aligned:
     • fraction       : 0..1 along the treasure route (harbor→treasure).
     • currentPhase   : 0..6 = phase the ship is currently IN;
                        7     = all phases done, treasure claimed.
     • localProgress  : 0..1, how much of currentPhase is cleared (ignored
                        when currentPhase === 7).
   solvedProblems / totalProblems only populate the captain's-log count —
   they don't affect ship position. */
function updateVoyage(fraction, currentPhase, localProgress,
                     solvedProblems, totalProblems) {
  const path = document.getElementById("treasureRoute");
  const ship = document.getElementById("voyageShip");
  const xMark = document.getElementById("voyageXMark");
  const log  = document.getElementById("voyageLog");
  const ports = document.querySelectorAll('#voyagePorts .voyage-port');
  if (!path || !ship || !log || !ports.length) return;

  if (!_voyagePortsPlaced) placeVoyagePorts();

  const totalLen = path.getTotalLength();
  if (!totalLen) return;

  const clamped = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, fraction || 0));

  // Ship position along the curve in viewBox coords, converted to %.
  const shipLen = totalLen * clamped;
  const shipPt = path.getPointAtLength(shipLen);
  const xPct = (shipPt.x / _VB_W) * 100;
  const yPct = (shipPt.y / _VB_H) * 100;
  ship.style.left = xPct + "%";
  ship.style.top  = yPct + "%";

  // Tangent rotation — sample a nearby point on the path.
  const aheadLen = Math.min(totalLen, shipLen + 2);
  const aheadPt = path.getPointAtLength(aheadLen);
  // Important: SVG is stretched non-uniformly via preserveAspectRatio="none",
  // so we scale the tangent's dx/dy by the actual rendered stretch before
  // computing atan2 — that way the ship visually points along the drawn curve
  // rather than along the un-stretched viewBox curve.
  const stripEl = document.querySelector(".voyage-strip");
  let sx = 1, sy = 1;
  if (stripEl) {
    const r = stripEl.getBoundingClientRect();
    if (r.width > 0 && r.height > 0) {
      sx = r.width / _VB_W;
      sy = r.height / _VB_H;
    }
  }
  const dx = (aheadPt.x - shipPt.x) * sx;
  const dy = (aheadPt.y - shipPt.y) * sy;
  const angle = Math.atan2(dy, dx) * 180 / Math.PI;
  const rotor = ship.querySelector(".ship-rotor");
  if (rotor) rotor.style.transform = `translate(-50%, -50%) rotate(${angle.toFixed(2)}deg)`;

  // (Travelled-stroke overlay is gone — per-item dash segments now show
  // which items are solved independently of the ship's position.)

  // Ports light up as their phase is FULLY completed. Port i = phase i.
  // If currentPhase is N, phases 0..N-1 are done → ports 0..N-1 are visited.
  ports.forEach((p, i) => {
    p.classList.toggle("visited", i < currentPhase);
  });

  // Current-port highlight — the port the ship is currently sailing toward.
  // When currentPhase === 7 (all done), no port pulses — treasure has it.
  ports.forEach(p => p.classList.remove("current"));
  if (currentPhase >= 0 && currentPhase < 7) {
    ports[currentPhase]?.classList.add("current");
  }

  // X-marks-the-spot lights up only when all 7 phases are done.
  if (xMark) xMark.classList.toggle("claimed", currentPhase >= 7);

  // Fire the "arriving" pulse whenever the captain crosses into a new phase.
  if (currentPhase !== _voyageLastPhase && _voyageLastPhase !== -1) {
    ship.classList.remove("arriving");
    void ship.getBoundingClientRect();
    ship.classList.add("arriving");
    setTimeout(() => ship.classList.remove("arriving"), 1500);
  }
  _voyageLastPhase = currentPhase;

  // Captain's log line — describes the voyage state in plain language.
  let logMsg;
  const localPctNum = Math.round((localProgress || 0) * 100);
  if (totalProblems === 0) {
    logMsg = "Weighing anchor — departure harbor";
  } else if (currentPhase >= 7) {
    logMsg = `Treasure claimed — Captain of the Atlas · ${solvedProblems}/${totalProblems} total`;
  } else if (currentPhase === 0 && localPctNum === 0) {
    logMsg = `Casting off from harbor — bound for ${PHASE_LABELS[0].long}`;
  } else {
    const phaseLabel = PHASE_LABELS[currentPhase].long;
    logMsg = `Sailing ${phaseLabel} — ${localPctNum}% through this leg · ${solvedProblems}/${totalProblems} total`;
  }
  log.textContent = logMsg;
}

/* =====================================================================
   READING-PROGRESS bar
   ===================================================================== */
function onScroll() {
  const h = document.documentElement.scrollHeight - window.innerHeight;
  const pct = h > 0 ? window.scrollY / h : 0;
  $("#readbar").style.width = (pct * 100) + "%";
}
window.addEventListener("scroll", onScroll, { passive: true });

// Re-place the treasure-map ports + re-compute ship tangent on window resize.
// (SVG stretches to container width so the rendered curve changes shape.)
let _voyageResizeRaf = 0;
window.addEventListener("resize", () => {
  if (_voyageResizeRaf) cancelAnimationFrame(_voyageResizeRaf);
  _voyageResizeRaf = requestAnimationFrame(() => {
    _voyagePortsPlaced = false;
    placeVoyagePorts();
    updateProgress();
  });
});

// Live-refresh quiz chips + header counter whenever a quiz is answered/reset.
document.addEventListener("atlas:quiz-answered", () => {
  const nodes = $$("#guide details");
  computeAndPaintMeta(nodes.filter(n => n.dataset.title));
  updateProgress();
});

/* =====================================================================
   QUOTE POOLS — one pool per modal mode.
   Each quote: { t: text, a: author-in-small-caps }.
   ===================================================================== */

// Shown ONCE on first-ever landing (or after a full Reset). Big,
// beginner-friendly, anchor-weigh energy.
const WELCOME_QUOTES = [
  { t: "Welcome aboard, Captain. Seven seas lie ahead — and you have a map, a compass, and all the time in the world to sail them. Take the helm.",
    a: "First Entry · Captain's Log" },
  { t: "Every great captain stood on this deck for the first time once. Today, that captain is you. Cast off.",
    a: "First Entry · Captain's Log" },
  { t: "You don't need to capture the seven seas today. You need to raise the first sail. The rest will follow, one wave at a time.",
    a: "Navigator's Creed" },
  { t: "Somewhere past the seventh sea there is a query you cannot yet write. By the time you get there, it will feel small. Start here.",
    a: "First Entry · Captain's Log" },
  { t: "The Atlas has been charted for you. Your only job is to sail — and return tomorrow. That is how captains are made.",
    a: "Old Pilot's Rhyme" },
];

// Shown when the user opens the Atlas for the first time today AND their
// streak is intact (last visit was yesterday). Praise consistency.
const STREAK_QUOTES = [
  { t: "The crew sees you return, Captain — and the sails rise again. That is what a voyage is made of.",
    a: "Captain's Log" },
  { t: "Day by day you close on the treasure. Consistency is a stronger wind than talent.",
    a: "Navigator's Creed" },
  { t: "You came back. The compass steadies when you do. The seven seas cannot resist a captain who returns.",
    a: "Captain's Log" },
  { t: "Another day, another wave claimed. The Atlas fills its map with every captain who keeps their word.",
    a: "Old Pilot's Rhyme" },
  { t: "The crew cheered when they saw your lantern on the horizon. Good captains come back — and you did.",
    a: "Captain's Log" },
  { t: "Every day you sail, the seven seas grow kinder. You're not learning SQL anymore — you're becoming someone who knows it.",
    a: "Pirate's Proverb" },
  { t: "Consistency is the true treasure. The one you're carrying back to shore right now.",
    a: "Shipwright's Wisdom" },
  { t: "Another port in the ship's log. The ocean notices, Captain. So does the crew. So do you.",
    a: "Captain's Log" },
];

// Shown when the user returns after missing ≥ 1 day. Warm, not scolding —
// "the crew was clueless without you" energy. Invite them back to the wheel.
const BROKEN_QUOTES = [
  { t: "The crew was clueless without you, Captain. The sails slackened. The compass spun. Take the wheel — and let us sail again.",
    a: "First Mate's Log" },
  { t: "The ship drifted a little while you were ashore. No harm done — captains come home. Your map is waiting exactly where you left it.",
    a: "Navigator's Creed" },
  { t: "The horizon did not move. The treasure did not sail. Only you stepped off the deck — and here you are again. Welcome back.",
    a: "Captain's Log" },
  { t: "A broken streak is not a shipwreck, Captain. It's a port you visited. Untie the ropes and let us sail for the next sea.",
    a: "Old Pilot's Rhyme" },
  { t: "The crew stopped asking 'where is the captain?' the moment they saw you climb aboard. Chart the next course.",
    a: "First Mate's Log" },
  { t: "The seas missed you. The seven phases missed you. Your hands on this wheel are what made this a voyage. Now — raise the sails.",
    a: "Captain's Log" },
  { t: "Gone a day or gone a week — the Atlas is patient. It remembers every wave you sailed. Pick up where you left off.",
    a: "Shipwright's Wisdom" },
  { t: "Without the captain, the sails are just canvas. You're back. That's all the crew needed to hear.",
    a: "First Mate's Log" },
];

// Shown when every problem is solved AND every MCQ is correct.
const CONQUEROR_QUOTES = [
  { t: "You have charted every sea of SQL. The Atlas has no more maps to give you — you are the cartographer now.",
    a: "Captain's Last Entry" },
  { t: "Every port crossed. Every storm weathered. Every NULL shoal avoided. The horizon belongs to you.",
    a: "Captain's Last Entry" },
  { t: "You began this voyage a deckhand. You finish it with a steady compass, a full chart, and a crew who asks you for the plan.",
    a: "Captain's Last Entry" },
  { t: "The treasure was never in the SELECT. It was in the queries you had the courage to write. And write again.",
    a: "Pirate's Last Entry" },
  { t: "Seven phases, seven seas. The Atlas has been conquered. The captain has been forged.",
    a: "Captain's Last Entry" },
  { t: "You stand at the final port. Behind you: every pattern. Ahead: every interview you ever feared, now smaller than this deck.",
    a: "Captain's Last Entry" },
  { t: "The Jolly Roger flies for you tonight. You did not learn SQL — you mastered its seas.",
    a: "Pirate's Last Entry" },
];

function pickFrom(pool) {
  return pool[Math.floor(Math.random() * pool.length)];
}

/* =====================================================================
   STREAK ENGINE — tracks daily-visit streaks in localStorage and decides
   which modal to show on page load.
   ===================================================================== */
const LS_LAST_VISIT  = "atlas.lastVisitDate";   // "YYYY-MM-DD"
const LS_STREAK      = "atlas.streak";          // integer
const LS_BEST        = "atlas.bestStreak";      // integer
const LS_WELCOMED    = "atlas.welcomed";        // "1" once welcome shown
const LS_CONQ_SEEN   = "atlas.conquerorSeen";   // "1" once conqueror shown
const LS_CAPTAIN     = "atlas.captainName";     // captain's display name
const LS_VOYAGE_START= "atlas.voyageStart";     // ISO date when welcome committed
const LS_VOYAGE_END  = "atlas.voyageEnd";       // ISO date when conqueror earned
const LS_DAILY_QUOTE = "atlas.dailyQuote";      // JSON: {date,mode,t,a} — replayed in manual mode

/* Persist the quote picked for today's first-visit modal so re-opening the
   voyage map later the same day shows the same line instead of a new random
   one. Stored as `{ date: "YYYY-MM-DD", mode, t, a }`. */
function saveDailyQuote(mode, quote) {
  try {
    localStorage.setItem(LS_DAILY_QUOTE, JSON.stringify({
      date: _todayKey(), mode, t: quote.t || "", a: quote.a || ""
    }));
  } catch (_) {}
}
/* Read today's stored quote, or null if none / stale (different date). */
function loadDailyQuote() {
  try {
    const raw = localStorage.getItem(LS_DAILY_QUOTE);
    if (!raw) return null;
    const obj = JSON.parse(raw);
    if (!obj || obj.date !== _todayKey()) return null;
    return obj;
  } catch (_) { return null; }
}

function getCaptainName() {
  try { return (localStorage.getItem(LS_CAPTAIN) || "").trim(); } catch (_) { return ""; }
}
function setCaptainName(name) {
  try { localStorage.setItem(LS_CAPTAIN, String(name).trim()); } catch (_) {}
}
/* Format "Captain {Name}" when we have a name, else just "Captain". */
function captainAddress() {
  const n = getCaptainName();
  return n ? `Captain ${n}` : "Captain";
}
/* Human-readable date like "25 Apr 2026". Stable across locales. */
function formatVoyageDate(iso) {
  if (!iso) return "—";
  const d = new Date(iso);
  if (isNaN(d.getTime())) return iso;
  const mon = ["Jan","Feb","Mar","Apr","May","Jun","Jul","Aug","Sep","Oct","Nov","Dec"][d.getMonth()];
  return `${d.getDate()} ${mon} ${d.getFullYear()}`;
}
/* Inclusive day count between two ISO dates (both as YYYY-MM-DD). */
function voyageDurationDays(startIso, endIso) {
  if (!startIso || !endIso) return 0;
  const s = new Date(startIso + "T00:00:00").getTime();
  const e = new Date(endIso   + "T00:00:00").getTime();
  if (isNaN(s) || isNaN(e)) return 0;
  return Math.max(1, Math.round((e - s) / 86400000) + 1);
}

function _todayKey(d = new Date()) {
  // Local-date YYYY-MM-DD so travel/timezones don't break the streak.
  const y = d.getFullYear();
  const m = String(d.getMonth() + 1).padStart(2, "0");
  const day = String(d.getDate()).padStart(2, "0");
  return `${y}-${m}-${day}`;
}
function _yesterdayKey() {
  const d = new Date();
  d.setDate(d.getDate() - 1);
  return _todayKey(d);
}

/*  Returns an object describing what popup (if any) should show on landing:
 *    { mode: 'welcome' | 'daily-maintained' | 'daily-broken' | 'none',
 *      streak: <int>, best: <int>, prevStreak?: <int>, today: 'YYYY-MM-DD' }
 */
function computeStreakState() {
  const today = _todayKey();
  let last, streak, best, welcomed;
  try {
    last     = localStorage.getItem(LS_LAST_VISIT);
    streak   = parseInt(localStorage.getItem(LS_STREAK) || "0", 10) || 0;
    best     = parseInt(localStorage.getItem(LS_BEST)   || "0", 10) || 0;
    welcomed = localStorage.getItem(LS_WELCOMED) === "1";
  } catch (_) {
    last = null; streak = 0; best = 0; welcomed = false;
  }
  // First-ever landing (or reset).
  if (!welcomed || !last) {
    return { mode: "welcome", streak: 0, best, today };
  }
  // Already opened today — nothing to do.
  if (last === today) {
    return { mode: "none", streak, best, today };
  }
  // Came back yesterday → streak maintained (+1).
  if (last === _yesterdayKey()) {
    const next = streak + 1;
    return { mode: "daily-maintained", streak: next, best: Math.max(best, next), today, prevStreak: streak };
  }
  // Gap > 1 day → streak reset to 1. Remember the old streak for the modal text.
  return { mode: "daily-broken", streak: 1, best, today, prevStreak: streak };
}

/*  Commit the computed state to localStorage. Call after the popup decision
 *  so the state is saved even if the user closes the modal immediately. */
function commitVisit(state) {
  try {
    localStorage.setItem(LS_LAST_VISIT, state.today);
    localStorage.setItem(LS_STREAK, String(state.streak));
    localStorage.setItem(LS_BEST,   String(state.best));
    if (state.mode === "welcome") {
      localStorage.setItem(LS_WELCOMED, "1");
      // Stamp the voyage start date once, on first welcome landing.
      if (!localStorage.getItem(LS_VOYAGE_START)) {
        localStorage.setItem(LS_VOYAGE_START, state.today);
      }
    }
  } catch (_) {}
}

/* =====================================================================
   UNIFIED VOYAGE MODAL — one modal, four modes (welcome, daily-maintained,
   daily-broken, conqueror) + one "manual" re-open mode.
   ===================================================================== */
function _setText(id, text) {
  const el = document.getElementById(id);
  if (el) el.textContent = text;
}

/*  Animate the big streak digit from 0 → target like a counter ticking. */
function _tickStreakNumber(target) {
  const el = document.getElementById("streakNum");
  if (!el) return;
  const dur = Math.min(1400, 350 + target * 120); // faster for big streaks
  const start = performance.now();
  function step(now) {
    const t = Math.min(1, (now - start) / dur);
    // ease-out-cubic
    const e = 1 - Math.pow(1 - t, 3);
    el.textContent = String(Math.round(target * e));
    if (t < 1) requestAnimationFrame(step);
    else el.textContent = String(target);
  }
  el.textContent = "0";
  requestAnimationFrame(step);
}

/*  Render the modal in the given mode.
 *    mode: 'welcome' | 'daily-maintained' | 'daily-broken' | 'conqueror' | 'manual'
 *    ctx:  { streak, best, prevStreak, problemTotal, quizTotal }  (mode-specific) */
function openVoyageModal(mode, ctx = {}) {
  const scrim = document.getElementById("voyageScrim");
  if (!scrim || scrim.classList.contains("open")) return;
  scrim.setAttribute("data-mode", mode);

  // Captain address — falls back to bare "Captain" until a name is entered.
  const addr = captainAddress();
  const name = getCaptainName();

  // Title / subtitle / crown / CTA / quote pool per mode.
  let crown = "⚓", title = `Welcome Aboard, ${addr}`,
      sub   = "Seven seas ahead · One wave at a time",
      cta   = "Set sail",
      quote = pickFrom(WELCOME_QUOTES);

  if (mode === "daily-maintained") {
    crown = "🔥";
    title = `You Came Back, ${addr}`;
    sub   = `Day ${ctx.streak} of the voyage · Streak intact`;
    cta   = name ? `Back to the helm, ${name}` : "Back to the helm";
    quote = pickFrom(STREAK_QUOTES);
  } else if (mode === "daily-broken") {
    crown = "🏴‍☠️";
    title = `${addr} on Deck`;
    sub   = ctx.prevStreak > 1
      ? `The ${ctx.prevStreak}-day streak broke · Starting a new one at Day 1`
      : `A new voyage begins · Day 1`;
    cta   = "Take the wheel";
    quote = pickFrom(BROKEN_QUOTES);
  } else if (mode === "conqueror") {
    crown = "👑";
    title = name ? `${name}, Captain of the Atlas` : "Captain of the Atlas";
    sub   = "All seven seas charted · Every port anchored";
    cta   = "Hoist the Jolly Roger";
    quote = pickFrom(CONQUEROR_QUOTES);
  } else if (mode === "manual") {
    crown = "⛵";
    title = name ? `${name}'s Voyage So Far` : "Your Voyage So Far";
    sub   = "The seven seas, charted by your progress";
    cta   = "Close";
    // Manual re-open — replay the quote picked earlier today. If nothing's
    // stored yet (user clicked the map before the daily popup fired, or the
    // store got wiped), pick one now based on current streak state and save
    // it so the rest of the day is consistent.
    const stored = loadDailyQuote();
    if (stored && (stored.t || stored.a)) {
      quote = { t: stored.t, a: stored.a };
    } else {
      let pool = WELCOME_QUOTES;
      try {
        const s = parseInt(localStorage.getItem(LS_STREAK) || "0", 10) || 0;
        const last = localStorage.getItem(LS_LAST_VISIT);
        const today = _todayKey();
        const yest  = _yesterdayKey();
        if (localStorage.getItem(LS_CONQ_SEEN) === "1") pool = CONQUEROR_QUOTES;
        else if (last === today && s > 1) pool = STREAK_QUOTES;
        else if (last && last !== today && last !== yest) pool = BROKEN_QUOTES;
      } catch (_) {}
      quote = pickFrom(pool);
      saveDailyQuote("manual", quote);
    }
  }

  // For first-of-day modes (welcome / daily-maintained / daily-broken /
  // conqueror), persist the quote so manual re-opens the rest of the day
  // show the same line instead of a fresh random pick.
  if (mode === "welcome" || mode === "daily-maintained"
      || mode === "daily-broken" || mode === "conqueror") {
    saveDailyQuote(mode, quote);
  }

  _setText("voyageCrown",  crown);
  _setText("voyageTitle",  title);
  _setText("voyageSub",    sub);
  _setText("voyageQuote",  quote.t);
  _setText("voyageAuthor", quote.a);
  const btn = document.getElementById("voyageBtn");
  if (btn) btn.textContent = cta;

  // Pre-fill the captain name field if we already know it (e.g. after Reset
  // clears the name, or a rare edge-case where welcome shows twice).
  if (mode === "welcome") {
    const input = document.getElementById("captainNameInput");
    const cap   = document.getElementById("voyageNameCapture");
    if (input) input.value = name || "";
    if (cap)   cap.classList.remove("is-error");
    // Focus the input once the modal is on-screen.
    requestAnimationFrame(() => input?.focus());
  }

  // Streak section (daily modes only).
  if (mode === "daily-maintained" || mode === "daily-broken") {
    _setText("streakLbl", mode === "daily-broken" ? "Day 1 · New voyage" : "Day Streak");
    const best = ctx.best || 0;
    let foot;
    if (mode === "daily-broken") {
      foot = ctx.prevStreak > 1
        ? `Best ever: ${best} days. Let's chase it again${name ? `, ${name}` : ""}.`
        : `Best ever: ${best} days. A fresh sail.`;
    } else {
      foot = ctx.streak === best
        ? `New personal best — keep sailing${name ? `, ${name}` : ", Captain"}.`
        : `Best ever: ${best} days`;
    }
    _setText("streakFoot", foot);
    _tickStreakNumber(ctx.streak || 0);
  }

  // Conqueror — stats + captain log (name + start/end dates + duration).
  if (mode === "conqueror") {
    _setText("conqStatProblems", String(ctx.problemTotal || 0));
    _setText("conqStatMcqs",     String(ctx.quizTotal    || 0));
    let startIso = null, endIso = null;
    try {
      startIso = localStorage.getItem(LS_VOYAGE_START);
      endIso   = localStorage.getItem(LS_VOYAGE_END);
    } catch (_) {}
    // Ensure we have an end date — set it now on first conqueror landing.
    if (!endIso) {
      endIso = _todayKey();
      try { localStorage.setItem(LS_VOYAGE_END, endIso); } catch (_) {}
    }
    // Fallback if a voyage start was never stamped (shouldn't happen, but
    // safe): treat today as both start and end.
    if (!startIso) startIso = endIso;
    _setText("conqCaptainName", name || "Unnamed Captain");
    _setText("conqDateStart",   formatVoyageDate(startIso));
    _setText("conqDateEnd",     formatVoyageDate(endIso));
    const days = voyageDurationDays(startIso, endIso);
    _setText("conqDuration",
      days === 1
        ? `One day at sea · Seven seas claimed in a single voyage`
        : `${days} days at sea · Seven seas claimed`);
  }

  scrim.classList.add("open");
  scrim.setAttribute("aria-hidden", "false");

  // The treasure map needs one layout pass to get path length. Re-place the
  // ports + update ship position after the modal is visible.
  requestAnimationFrame(() => {
    _voyagePortsPlaced = false;
    // Force segments to rebuild — the modal-embedded SVG is a different
    // rendered instance so path lengths need a fresh read.
    _voyageSegCount = 0;
    const segGroup = document.getElementById("voyageSegments");
    if (segGroup) delete segGroup.dataset.segSig;   // bust the cache-key
    placeVoyagePorts();
    if (typeof _lastProgress === "object" && _lastProgress) {
      if (Array.isArray(_lastProgress.phaseBuckets)) {
        rebuildVoyageSegments(_lastProgress.phaseBuckets);
        paintVoyageSegments(
          _lastProgress.phaseBuckets,
          _lastProgress.currentPhase
        );
      }
      updateVoyage(
        _lastProgress.frac ?? 0,
        (_lastProgress.currentPhase != null ? _lastProgress.currentPhase : 0),
        _lastProgress.localProgress ?? 0,
        _lastProgress.solved || 0,
        _lastProgress.total  || 0
      );
    } else {
      updateVoyage(0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
    }
  });
}

function hideVoyageModal() {
  const scrim = document.getElementById("voyageScrim");
  if (!scrim) return;
  scrim.classList.remove("open");
  scrim.setAttribute("aria-hidden", "true");
}

/* =====================================================================
   CONQUEROR CHECK — fires live when the last problem+MCQ lands.
   Also called on page load; shows once per session once earned.
   ===================================================================== */
let _conqueredThisSession = false;
function checkConqueror(problemTotal, problemSolved, quizTotal, quizCorrect) {
  if (problemTotal < 1 || quizTotal < 1) return;
  if (problemSolved < problemTotal || quizCorrect < quizTotal) return;
  if (_conqueredThisSession) return;
  _conqueredThisSession = true;
  // Close any existing modal first so conqueror takes priority.
  hideVoyageModal();
  setTimeout(() => {
    openVoyageModal("conqueror", {
      problemTotal, quizTotal
    });
    try { localStorage.setItem(LS_CONQ_SEEN, "1"); } catch (_) {}
  }, 200);
}

// Cached progress numbers so openVoyageModal can repaint the map without
// running the full updateProgress pipeline.
let _lastProgress = null;

/* Sidebar streak chip — kept in sync with storage so users see their streak
   even when no popup is open. */
function paintSidebarStreak() {
  const val  = document.getElementById("streakSidebarVal");
  const chip = document.getElementById("streakSidebarChip");
  let streak = 0, last = null;
  try {
    streak = parseInt(localStorage.getItem(LS_STREAK) || "0", 10) || 0;
    last   = localStorage.getItem(LS_LAST_VISIT);
  } catch (_) {}
  // Show "cold" state if last visit wasn't today or yesterday (streak is
  // provisionally broken — will be reset next time they open).
  const today = _todayKey();
  const yest  = _yesterdayKey();
  const cold  = !last || (last !== today && last !== yest);
  if (val && chip) {
    val.textContent = String(streak);
    chip.classList.toggle("cold", cold);
  }
  // Also keep the mobile FAB streak badge in sync.
  const fabBadge = document.getElementById("fabStreak");
  if (fabBadge) {
    fabBadge.textContent = String(streak);
    fabBadge.classList.toggle("cold", cold);
  }
}

/* =====================================================================
   RENDER
   ===================================================================== */
function render() {
  const mdEl = $("#guide-md");
  if (!mdEl) return;
  const md = mdEl.textContent.trim();
  marked.setOptions({ gfm: true, breaks: false, headerIds: false, mangle: false });
  const guide = $("#guide");
  guide.innerHTML = marked.parse(md);
  decorate(guide);
  const nodes = buildTree(guide);
  computeAndPaintMeta(nodes);
  paintStars(guide);
  buildSidebar();
  updateProgress();
  paintResume();

  // Restore every <details> that the user had open before the last refresh.
  // Stored as a newline-joined list of IDs under `atlas.openSections`.
  // This is what makes "I had 2.1 expanded → refresh → 2.1 still expanded" work
  // even if the user never scrolled.
  try {
    const raw = localStorage.getItem("atlas.openSections") || "";
    const ids = raw.split("\n").filter(Boolean);
    for (const id of ids) {
      const el = document.getElementById(id);
      if (el && el.tagName === "DETAILS") el.open = true;
    }
  } catch (_) {}

  // deep link handling. Priority:
  //   1. explicit ?jump=<id> query (CTA from outside)
  //   2. URL #hash
  //   3. localStorage `atlas.lastSection` — auto-resume where the user last was
  const hash = location.hash.slice(1);
  const jumpParam = new URLSearchParams(location.search).get("jump");
  let target = jumpParam || hash;
  if (!target) {
    try { target = localStorage.getItem("atlas.lastSection") || ""; } catch (_) {}
  }
  if (target) {
    requestAnimationFrame(() => openTo(target));
  }
}

/* =====================================================================
   EVENT WIRING
   ===================================================================== */
document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
  render();

  // Paint the sidebar streak chip right away so users see their current
  // streak even before the welcome/daily modal is processed.
  paintSidebarStreak();

  // Unified voyage-modal wiring — X, scrim-click, Esc, CTA button all close.
  // The CTA button also captures the captain's name when we're in welcome mode.
  const scrim = document.getElementById("voyageScrim");

  /* Welcome-mode gate: require a non-empty captain name before closing.
     If empty, shake the input + show an error hint. */
  function attemptCloseFromCta() {
    if (scrim?.getAttribute("data-mode") === "welcome") {
      const input = document.getElementById("captainNameInput");
      const cap   = document.getElementById("voyageNameCapture");
      const hint  = document.getElementById("captainNameHint");
      const raw   = (input?.value || "").trim();
      if (!raw) {
        cap?.classList.add("is-error");
        if (hint) hint.textContent = "Every ship needs a captain. Give us a name before you sail.";
        input?.focus();
        return;
      }
      // Trim down to a tidy display name (max 32 chars, collapse whitespace).
      const clean = raw.replace(/\s+/g, " ").slice(0, 32);
      setCaptainName(clean);
    }
    hideVoyageModal();
  }

  document.getElementById("voyageClose")?.addEventListener("click", () => {
    // Dismiss via ✕ — if welcome, also save whatever's typed (even empty is
    // fine — they'll just be addressed as "Captain" until they enter one).
    if (scrim?.getAttribute("data-mode") === "welcome") {
      const input = document.getElementById("captainNameInput");
      const raw   = (input?.value || "").trim();
      if (raw) setCaptainName(raw.replace(/\s+/g, " ").slice(0, 32));
    }
    hideVoyageModal();
  });
  document.getElementById("voyageBtn")?.addEventListener("click", attemptCloseFromCta);
  scrim?.addEventListener("click", (e) => { if (e.target === scrim) attemptCloseFromCta(); });
  window.addEventListener("keydown", (e) => {
    if (e.key === "Escape" && scrim?.classList.contains("open")) attemptCloseFromCta();
  });

  // Enter key inside the captain-name input → submit (same as the CTA).
  document.getElementById("captainNameInput")?.addEventListener("keydown", (e) => {
    if (e.key === "Enter") { e.preventDefault(); attemptCloseFromCta(); }
  });
  // Clear the error hint as soon as they start typing.
  document.getElementById("captainNameInput")?.addEventListener("input", () => {
    const cap  = document.getElementById("voyageNameCapture");
    const hint = document.getElementById("captainNameHint");
    if (cap?.classList.contains("is-error")) {
      cap.classList.remove("is-error");
      if (hint) hint.textContent = "The crew will need to know who's at the helm.";
    }
  });

  // Manual re-open from the sidebar "⛵ Voyage Map" button.
  document.getElementById("openVoyage")?.addEventListener("click", () => {
    openVoyageModal("manual");
  });

  // Daily popup decision — runs ONCE per calendar day on first landing.
  // Welcome → daily-maintained → daily-broken based on visit-history.
  // Conqueror popup has priority and fires from checkConqueror() instead.
  (function showEntryPopup() {
    const state = computeStreakState();
    if (state.mode === "none") return;              // already visited today
    if (_conqueredThisSession) return;              // conqueror has priority
    commitVisit(state);                             // save before showing
    paintSidebarStreak();
    // Defer slightly so the hero + sidebar finish painting first.
    setTimeout(() => {
      openVoyageModal(state.mode, {
        streak: state.streak,
        best: state.best,
        prevStreak: state.prevStreak
      });
    }, 350);
  })();

  // search
  $("#search").addEventListener("input", (e) => {
    clearTimeout(searchTimer);
    const v = e.target.value;
    searchTimer = setTimeout(() => applySearch(v), 120);
  });

  // facets
  $("#facetBar").addEventListener("click", (e) => {
    const b = e.target.closest(".facet");
    if (!b) return;
    applyFacet(b.dataset.facet);
  });

  // expand / collapse
  $("#expandAll").addEventListener("click", () => $$("#guide details").forEach(d => d.open = true));
  $("#collapseAll").addEventListener("click", () => $$("#guide details").forEach(d => d.open = false));
  // ---- Reset flow: open the confirmation modal instead of native confirm() ----
  function performReset() {
    Object.keys(localStorage).filter(k =>
      k.startsWith("atlas.status.") || k.startsWith("atlas.quiz.")
      || k === "atlas.lastSlug" || k === "atlas.lastSection" || k === "atlas.openSections"
      // Also clear streak/welcome/captain/voyage flags so reset restarts the voyage.
      || k === LS_LAST_VISIT || k === LS_STREAK || k === LS_BEST
      || k === LS_WELCOMED  || k === LS_CONQ_SEEN
      || k === LS_CAPTAIN   || k === LS_VOYAGE_START || k === LS_VOYAGE_END
      || k === LS_DAILY_QUOTE
    ).forEach(k => localStorage.removeItem(k));
    _conqueredThisSession = false;
    $$("#guide details").forEach(d => { delete d.dataset.status; });
    // Visually un-lock every quiz so UI matches the cleared storage.
    $$(".quiz.is-answered").forEach(q => {
      q.classList.remove("is-answered");
      q.querySelectorAll(".quiz-opts > li").forEach(li => {
        li.classList.remove("is-locked", "is-correct", "is-wrong");
      });
      const hint = q.querySelector(".quiz-hint");
      if (hint) hint.textContent = "Pick an option to reveal the explanation.";
    });
    const nodes = $$("#guide details");
    computeAndPaintMeta(nodes.filter(n => n.dataset.title));
    updateProgress();
    paintResume();
    paintSidebarStreak();
    // Re-show the welcome modal so the voyage feels freshly started.
    setTimeout(() => {
      const state = computeStreakState();
      commitVisit(state);
      paintSidebarStreak();
      openVoyageModal(state.mode, state);
    }, 220);
  }

  const resetScrim = document.getElementById("resetScrim");
  function openResetModal() {
    if (!resetScrim) return;
    resetScrim.classList.add("open");
    resetScrim.setAttribute("aria-hidden", "false");
    // Give keyboard focus to the safe (cancel) button so Enter doesn't scuttle.
    setTimeout(() => document.getElementById("resetCancel")?.focus(), 30);
  }
  function closeResetModal() {
    if (!resetScrim) return;
    resetScrim.classList.remove("open");
    resetScrim.setAttribute("aria-hidden", "true");
  }

  $("#resetProg").addEventListener("click", openResetModal);
  document.getElementById("resetCancel")?.addEventListener("click", closeResetModal);
  document.getElementById("resetCloseBtn")?.addEventListener("click", closeResetModal);
  document.getElementById("resetConfirm")?.addEventListener("click", () => {
    closeResetModal();
    performReset();
  });
  resetScrim?.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
    if (e.target === resetScrim) closeResetModal();
  });
  window.addEventListener("keydown", (e) => {
    if (e.key === "Escape" && resetScrim?.classList.contains("open")) closeResetModal();
  });

  // Mobile floating action button — re-opens the voyage map on small screens
  // where the sidebar (and its "⛵ Voyage Map" button) is hidden.
  document.getElementById("voyageFab")?.addEventListener("click", () => {
    openVoyageModal("manual");
  });

  // ⌘K
  $("#paletteOpen").addEventListener("click", openPalette);
  $("#paletteInput").addEventListener("input", (e) => renderPalette(e.target.value));
  $("#paletteInput").addEventListener("keydown", (e) => {
    const list = $("#paletteList");
    const items = [...list.querySelectorAll(".palette-item[data-id]")];
    const idx = items.findIndex(i => i.classList.contains("active"));
    if (e.key === "ArrowDown") {
      e.preventDefault();
      if (idx < items.length - 1) { items[idx]?.classList.remove("active"); items[idx + 1]?.classList.add("active"); }
    } else if (e.key === "ArrowUp") {
      e.preventDefault();
      if (idx > 0) { items[idx]?.classList.remove("active"); items[idx - 1]?.classList.add("active"); }
    } else if (e.key === "Enter") {
      const id = items.find(i => i.classList.contains("active"))?.dataset.id;
      if (id) { closePalette(); openTo(id); }
    } else if (e.key === "Escape") closePalette();
  });
  $("#palette").addEventListener("click", (e) => {
    if (e.target.id === "palette") closePalette();
  });
  window.addEventListener("keydown", (e) => {
    if ((e.metaKey || e.ctrlKey) && e.key.toLowerCase() === "k") {
      e.preventDefault(); openPalette();
    } else if (e.key === "/" && document.activeElement === document.body) {
      e.preventDefault(); $("#search").focus();
    }
  });

  // practice click — record last slug for resume
  $("#guide").addEventListener("click", (e) => {
    const a = e.target.closest("a.practice-pill");
    if (a?.dataset.slug) {
      localStorage.setItem("atlas.lastSlug", a.dataset.slug);
      // mark attempted if not already
      if (getStatus(a.dataset.slug) === "todo") setStatus(a.dataset.slug, "attempted");
    }
  });

  // Star toggle — event delegation on the guide. `capture:true` lets us
  // preventDefault BEFORE the <summary>'s native toggle fires, so starring
  // doesn't also collapse or expand the node.
  $("#guide").addEventListener("click", (e) => {
    const btn = e.target.closest(".star-btn");
    if (!btn) return;
    e.preventDefault();
    e.stopPropagation();
    const node = btn.closest(".phase-node, .section-node, .subnode");
    if (!node || !node.id) return;
    const on = !isStarred(node.id);
    setStarred(node.id, on);
    btn.classList.toggle("starred", on);
    btn.textContent = on ? "★" : "☆";
    if (on) node.dataset.starred = "1";
    else    delete node.dataset.starred;
    // Re-apply current facet so the starred-only filter updates live.
    if (activeFacet === "starred") applyFacet("starred");
  }, true);

  // Persist the set of open <details> so a refresh restores exactly the
  // nodes the user had expanded. Uses event delegation on #guide with
  // `capture: true` because `toggle` doesn't bubble.
  let openPersistTimer = null;
  function persistOpenSections() {
    clearTimeout(openPersistTimer);
    openPersistTimer = setTimeout(() => {
      try {
        const ids = $$("#guide details[open]").map(d => d.id).filter(Boolean);
        localStorage.setItem("atlas.openSections", ids.join("\n"));
      } catch (_) {}
    }, 120);
  }
  $("#guide").addEventListener("toggle", (e) => {
    if (e.target && e.target.tagName === "DETAILS") persistOpenSections();
  }, true);
  // Expand/Collapse-all + Reset also need to rewrite the snapshot.
  $("#expandAll").addEventListener("click", persistOpenSections);
  $("#collapseAll").addEventListener("click", persistOpenSections);

  // Track the last-viewed section. An IntersectionObserver watches every
  // phase / section / subnode summary-bearing node; whichever one is closest
  // to the top of the viewport is persisted as `atlas.lastSection`. Also
  // update on explicit navigation (sidebar / palette → openTo).
  function installLastSectionTracker() {
    const candidates = $$("#guide .phase-node, #guide .section-node, #guide .subnode")
      .filter(n => n.id);
    if (!candidates.length || !window.IntersectionObserver) return;

    // We want the topmost section currently intersecting the viewport.
    // Use a narrow band near the top so "whichever one is just below the
    // toolbar" wins — matches how most docs sites track current section.
    const visible = new Set();
    let saveTimer = null;
    const rootMargin = "-80px 0px -70% 0px";
    const io = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
      for (const e of entries) {
        if (e.isIntersecting) visible.add(e.target);
        else visible.delete(e.target);
      }
      if (!visible.size) return;
      // Pick the target with the smallest top offset (topmost in reading order).
      let best = null, bestTop = Infinity;
      visible.forEach(el => {
        const top = el.getBoundingClientRect().top;
        if (top < bestTop) { bestTop = top; best = el; }
      });
      if (!best || !best.id) return;
      clearTimeout(saveTimer);
      saveTimer = setTimeout(() => {
        try { localStorage.setItem("atlas.lastSection", best.id); } catch (_) {}
      }, 250);
    }, { rootMargin, threshold: [0, 0.01] });
    candidates.forEach(n => io.observe(n));
  }
  // Defer until the tree is fully painted.
  requestAnimationFrame(() => requestAnimationFrame(installLastSectionTracker));

  // Centralised refresh — repaints every status-dependent surface. Exposed on
  // `window` so the sandbox overlay (same-document, so `storage` events never
  // fire) can invoke it directly when a problem is passed or the overlay closes.
  function refreshAtlasProgress() {
    const nodes = $$("#guide details");
    computeAndPaintMeta(nodes.filter(n => n.dataset.title));
    paintPillStatuses(document.getElementById("guide"));
    updateProgress();
    paintResume();
  }
  window.refreshAtlasProgress = refreshAtlasProgress;

  // storage event — fires only for cross-document writes (sandbox opened in
  // a separate tab).
  window.addEventListener("storage", (e) => {
    if (e.key?.startsWith("atlas.status.")) refreshAtlasProgress();
  });
  // Same-tab bridge — the in-page sandbox overlay dispatches this custom event
  // after writing `atlas.status.<slug>`, since `storage` events are silent in
  // the same document.
  window.addEventListener("atlas:status-change", () => refreshAtlasProgress());
  // Also refresh on tab-visible (in case sandbox ran in a popup).
  document.addEventListener("visibilitychange", () => {
    if (document.visibilityState === "visible") refreshAtlasProgress();
  });
});
</script>
<!-- ================= EMBEDDED GUIDE MARKDOWN (populated by patch_atlas.py) ================= -->
<script id="guide-md" type="text/markdown"># How to Read This Atlas

> *The fastest way to master SQL in interview-ready shape.*

**Who this is for.** You can write `SELECT … FROM … WHERE …` but Hard-tier problems still stump you. This atlas gives you the **patterns** behind those problems, the **intuition** for each, and a browser sandbox to solve them end-to-end.

### Emoji legend — used consistently throughout

| Icon | Meaning |
|---|---|
| 🧠 | **Intuition** — the one-sentence mental model. Read this first. |
| ⚙️ | **Mechanics** — how the engine actually executes it. |
| ⚠️ | **Gotcha** — silent bug, wrong answer, or portability trap. |
| 💡 | **Tip** — a practical rule of thumb or dialect note. |
| 📝 | **Sample Problem** — a worked LeetCode-style example. |
| 🔗 | **Practice** — problems in the sandbox that drill this pattern. |

### Recommended path for a first-time reader

1. **Phase 0** — mental model (logical order, NULL, types). *Skipping this breaks everything downstream.*
2. **Phase 2.1 – 2.5** — aggregation, CTEs, self-joins, anti-joins. 80% of Easy/Medium problems live here.
3. **Phase 3.1 – 3.3** — ranking, LAG/LEAD, window frames. 80% of Medium/Hard.
4. **Phase 4.1** — gaps & islands. The single most-asked "Hard" pattern.
5. **Phase 5.1 – 5.2** — dates and string aggregation. Small syntax, huge interview surface area.
6. Everything else is reach-for-when-needed. The **Pattern Selection Decision Tree** at the bottom tells you which section matches your problem you're staring at.

### How to use the sandbox

Every 🔗 Practice link opens a problem in an in-browser SQLite. Type your query, hit **Run**, and a **hidden edge-case validator** compares your output against a gold query across multiple datasets — not just the visible sample. A ✅ means your query handles ties, NULLs, empty groups, and boundary cases, not just the happy path. No account. No setup. Progress saves in your browser.

### Keyboard shortcuts

| Key | Action |
|---|---|
| `⌘K` / `Ctrl+K` | Jump palette — fuzzy-search any phase, section, or problem |
| `/` | Focus the filter box |
| `?j` | Jump to the next section |
| `?k` | Jump to the previous section |

---
---

# PHASE 0 — The Mental Model

> *Before writing any SQL, understand how the engine thinks.*

---

## 0.1 SQL Logical Order of Execution

Many bugs come from assuming `SELECT` runs before `WHERE`.

```
1. FROM / JOIN    → Assemble the raw data set
2. WHERE          → Filter individual rows
3. GROUP BY       → Collapse rows into groups
4. HAVING         → Filter groups
5. SELECT         → Evaluate expressions, aliases
6. DISTINCT       → Remove duplicate rows
7. ORDER BY       → Sort (first place aliases are usable)
8. LIMIT / OFFSET → Truncate the result
```

🧠 **Why this matters:**
- You **cannot** reference a `SELECT` alias in `WHERE` — `WHERE` runs first.
- You **can** reference it in `ORDER BY` — `ORDER BY` runs after `SELECT`.
- Window functions run during `SELECT`, so you cannot filter on them in `WHERE` — wrap in a CTE first.
- `HAVING` can use aggregate expressions; `WHERE` cannot.

💡 **"Creating" an alias happens in step 5; "referencing" one only becomes legal from step 7 onward.** That's the whole trick — the alias exists in the output tuple by the time `ORDER BY` runs, but `WHERE` was evaluated two steps earlier when the alias was still just a piece of text.

**Can I use a SELECT alias here?**

| Clause | Alias usable? | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `WHERE` | ❌ | Runs before `SELECT`. Repeat the expression or wrap in a subquery/CTE. |
| `GROUP BY` | ⚠️ Engine-specific | MySQL/PostgreSQL allow it; SQL Server/Oracle do not. |
| `HAVING` | ⚠️ Engine-specific | MySQL allows; ANSI forbids. Safest: repeat the aggregate. |
| `SELECT` (same list) | ❌ | Cannot reference a sibling alias; use a CTE or subquery. |
| `ORDER BY` | ✅ | Runs after `SELECT`; aliases and positional numbers both work. |
| `LIMIT` / `OFFSET` | ✅ | Runs last. |

<div class="quiz" data-quiz-id="q-logical-order-1">
  <div class="quiz-kind">Theory</div>
  <div class="quiz-q">Which single clause is evaluated <em>last</em> in the logical-order model?</div>
  <ol class="quiz-opts">
    <li><code>SELECT</code></li>
    <li><code>ORDER BY</code></li>
    <li data-correct><code>LIMIT</code> / <code>OFFSET</code></li>
    <li><code>HAVING</code></li>
  </ol>
  <div class="quiz-why"><strong>LIMIT / OFFSET</strong> is the very last step. That's why <code>ORDER BY</code> applies <em>before</em> the slice — and why a query without <code>ORDER BY + LIMIT</code> can return rows in any order even if the outer row set looks sorted.</div>
</div>

<div class="quiz" data-quiz-id="q-logical-order-2">
  <div class="quiz-kind">Scenario</div>
  <div class="quiz-q">You wrote <code>SELECT salary * 12 AS annual FROM Emp WHERE annual &gt; 100000;</code> and got an "unknown column: annual" error. Why?</div>
  <ol class="quiz-opts">
    <li><code>WHERE</code> doesn't accept arithmetic expressions</li>
    <li data-correct><code>WHERE</code> runs before <code>SELECT</code>, so the <code>annual</code> alias doesn't exist yet</li>
    <li>You must quote alias names in <code>WHERE</code> as <code>"annual"</code></li>
    <li>The alias collides with a reserved keyword</li>
  </ol>
  <div class="quiz-why">Because <code>SELECT</code> runs <em>after</em> <code>WHERE</code>, <code>WHERE</code> only sees the raw table columns. Fix: repeat the expression (<code>WHERE salary*12 &gt; 100000</code>) or wrap in a CTE/subquery that materializes the alias first. <code>ORDER BY</code> works with aliases because it runs <em>after</em> <code>SELECT</code>.</div>
</div>

---

## 0.2 NULL Semantics & Three-Valued Logic

SQL uses **TRUE / FALSE / UNKNOWN** — not just true/false. Any comparison involving NULL yields UNKNOWN.

```
NULL = NULL      → UNKNOWN  (not TRUE!)
NULL <> NULL     → UNKNOWN  (not TRUE!)
NULL > 5         → UNKNOWN
NOT UNKNOWN      → UNKNOWN
TRUE AND UNKNOWN → UNKNOWN
TRUE OR UNKNOWN  → TRUE
FALSE AND UNKNOWN → FALSE
```

🧠 **The golden rule:** NULL means "unknown/missing." You can't compare an unknown to anything — the result is unknown.

⚠️ **WHERE and HAVING discard UNKNOWN:** Only rows where the condition is TRUE pass through. `WHERE col = NULL` returns **zero rows**, even if NULLs exist.

### Correct NULL Checks

```sql
-- WRONG ❌
WHERE col = NULL
WHERE col != NULL

-- RIGHT ✅
WHERE col IS NULL
WHERE col IS NOT NULL
```

### NULL Behavior Across Operations

| Context | NULL Behavior | Surprise Factor |
|---|---|---|
| `=`, `<>`, `<`, `>` | Any comparison with NULL → UNKNOWN | 🔴 High |
| `IN (1, 2, NULL)` | `3 IN (1, 2, NULL)` → UNKNOWN, not FALSE | 🔴 High |
| `NOT IN (1, 2, NULL)` | **Always UNKNOWN** → returns NO rows | 🔴 Critical |
| `COUNT(*)` | Counts all rows including NULLs | 🟡 Medium |
| `COUNT(col)` | Skips NULL values | 🟡 Medium |
| `SUM`, `AVG`, `MIN`, `MAX` | Skip NULLs entirely | 🟡 Medium |
| `AVG` denominator | NULLs excluded from count | 🔴 High |
| `GROUP BY` | NULLs grouped together (same group) | 🟡 Medium |
| `ORDER BY` | NULLs first or last (engine-dependent) | 🟡 Medium |
| `DISTINCT` | Multiple NULLs collapse to one NULL | 🟡 Medium |
| `UNION` | NULL = NULL for dedup purposes | 🔴 Contradicts `=` behavior |
| `CONCAT('a', NULL)` | Returns NULL (MySQL); 'a' (PostgreSQL `\|\|`) | 🔴 Engine-specific |
| Arithmetic: `5 + NULL` | NULL | 🟡 Medium |
| `CASE WHEN NULL THEN ...` | Falls through to ELSE | 🟡 Medium |

### NOT IN vs NOT EXISTS — The NULL Disaster

```sql
-- Subquery returns: (1, 2, NULL)
-- Query: WHERE id NOT IN (1, 2, NULL)
-- Evaluates: id <> 1 AND id <> 2 AND id <> NULL
--          = TRUE    AND TRUE    AND UNKNOWN
--          = UNKNOWN → row excluded!
-- Result: ZERO rows returned, no matter what!
```

Fix: always add `WHERE col IS NOT NULL` in the subquery, or use `NOT EXISTS`.

```sql
-- ❌ Silently returns zero rows if the subquery produces any NULL
SELECT * FROM customers
WHERE id NOT IN (SELECT customer_id FROM orders);

-- ✅ NULL-safe: NOT EXISTS checks row-by-row, NULL just means "no match"
SELECT * FROM customers c
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM orders o WHERE o.customer_id = c.id
);
```

💡 **Rule of thumb:** `NOT EXISTS` is the default choice for "rows without a match." Reach for `NOT IN` only when you've personally verified the subquery can never produce a `NULL`.

💡 **Why does `UNION` treat `NULL = NULL` as equal for deduplication, when `=` does not?** Different operations have different notions of equality: `=` is *truth-valued* (three-valued logic), but `UNION`, `GROUP BY`, `DISTINCT`, and `PARTITION BY` use *structural* equality — "do these tuples look identical?" — and NULL looks identical to NULL. The SQL standard picked structural equality for grouping because the alternative (never grouping NULLs together) would produce one row per NULL, which is almost never useful.

### NULL-Handling Functions

| Function | Behavior | Engine |
|---|---|---|
| `COALESCE(a, b, c)` | Returns first non-NULL value | All (ANSI SQL) |
| `IFNULL(a, b)` | If a is NULL, return b | MySQL |
| `ISNULL(a, b)` | If a is NULL, return b | SQL Server |
| `NVL(a, b)` | If a is NULL, return b | Oracle |
| `NULLIF(a, b)` | Returns NULL if a = b, else a | All |

```sql
-- COALESCE: chain of fallbacks
SELECT COALESCE(preferred_name, first_name, 'Unknown') AS display_name
FROM users;

-- NULLIF: prevent division by zero
SELECT revenue / NULLIF(cost, 0) AS ratio   -- returns NULL instead of error
FROM financials;

-- Replace NULL in AVG calculation
SELECT AVG(COALESCE(rating, 0)) AS avg_with_zeros  -- treats NULL as 0
FROM reviews;
```

### NULL in JOINs

```sql
-- NULL keys NEVER match in joins (NULL = NULL → UNKNOWN → no match)
SELECT *
FROM table_a a
JOIN table_b b ON a.key = b.key;   -- rows where a.key IS NULL are excluded
```

💡 If you need NULLs to match:
```sql
ON (a.key = b.key OR (a.key IS NULL AND b.key IS NULL))
-- Or: ON a.key IS NOT DISTINCT FROM b.key  (PostgreSQL)
```

💡 **`IS [NOT] DISTINCT FROM` — null-safe equality.** `a IS NOT DISTINCT FROM b` is `TRUE` when either both are equal **or** both are NULL — never UNKNOWN. Cleaner than the `OR (… IS NULL AND … IS NULL)` workaround. Supported by PostgreSQL, SQL Server 2022+, and BigQuery/Snowflake. MySQL has the `<=>` operator for the same semantics.

### ORDER BY with NULLs

```sql
-- MySQL: NULLs sort FIRST in ASC, LAST in DESC
-- PostgreSQL: NULLs sort LAST in ASC, FIRST in DESC (opposite!)

-- PostgreSQL: Control explicitly
ORDER BY col ASC NULLS LAST
ORDER BY col DESC NULLS FIRST

-- MySQL workaround:
ORDER BY col IS NULL, col ASC   -- pushes NULLs to end
```

<div class="quiz" data-quiz-id="q-null-count">
  <div class="quiz-kind">Guess the output</div>
  <div class="quiz-q">Given the <code>Users</code> table, what does the query return?</div>
  <div class="quiz-data-label">Users</div>
<pre><code>id | email
---+----------
 1 | a@x.io
 2 | NULL
 3 | c@x.io
 4 | NULL</code></pre>
<pre><code class="language-sql">SELECT COUNT(*), COUNT(email), COUNT(DISTINCT email)
FROM Users;</code></pre>
  <ol class="quiz-opts">
    <li><code>4, 4, 4</code></li>
    <li data-correct><code>4, 2, 2</code></li>
    <li><code>4, 2, 3</code></li>
    <li><code>NULL, NULL, NULL</code></li>
  </ol>
  <div class="quiz-why"><strong>COUNT(*)</strong> counts every row including NULLs → 4. <strong>COUNT(col)</strong> skips NULLs → 2. <strong>COUNT(DISTINCT col)</strong> skips NULLs <em>and</em> dedupes → 2 (a@x.io, c@x.io).</div>
</div>

<div class="quiz" data-quiz-id="q-null-not-in">
  <div class="quiz-kind">Scenario</div>
  <div class="quiz-q">You run <code>SELECT name FROM Cust WHERE id NOT IN (SELECT cust_id FROM Orders);</code> and get <em>zero</em> rows, even though many customers clearly have no orders. Why?</div>
  <ol class="quiz-opts">
    <li><code>NOT IN</code> requires a <code>JOIN</code>, not a subquery</li>
    <li data-correct>One of the <code>Orders.cust_id</code> values is NULL — so every comparison returns UNKNOWN, filtering every row out</li>
    <li>The inner subquery needs <code>DISTINCT</code></li>
    <li><code>NOT IN</code> is deprecated in modern SQL</li>
  </ol>
  <div class="quiz-why">Classic NULL trap. <code>x NOT IN (a, b, NULL)</code> is <code>x ≠ a AND x ≠ b AND x ≠ NULL</code>; the last comparison is UNKNOWN, which short-circuits the whole <code>AND</code> to UNKNOWN, so no row passes. Use <code>NOT EXISTS</code> (NULL-safe) or a <code>LEFT JOIN … WHERE o.id IS NULL</code> anti-join instead.</div>
</div>

<div class="quiz" data-quiz-id="q-null-eq">
  <div class="quiz-kind">Theory</div>
  <div class="quiz-q"><code>SELECT NULL = NULL;</code> returns:</div>
  <ol class="quiz-opts">
    <li><code>TRUE</code></li>
    <li><code>FALSE</code></li>
    <li data-correct><code>NULL</code> (UNKNOWN)</li>
    <li>Syntax error</li>
  </ol>
  <div class="quiz-why">Any comparison involving NULL yields UNKNOWN, which most engines surface as NULL. To test null-equality use <code>IS NULL</code> or <code>IS NOT DISTINCT FROM</code> (PostgreSQL) / <code>&lt;=&gt;</code> (MySQL).</div>
</div>

---

## 0.3 Type Casting & Implicit Conversions

⚠️ When you compare values of different types, SQL silently converts one. This causes:
1. **Wrong results** (string `'10' < '9'` lexicographically)
2. **Index bypass** (function on column = no index)

```sql
-- TRAP: varchar compared to int → MySQL converts VARCHAR to number
WHERE phone_number = 12345     -- converts '012345' to 12345, matches!
WHERE phone_number = '012345'  -- correct string comparison

-- TRAP: date compared to string
WHERE created_at = '2024-01-15'   -- OK: implicit cast to date
WHERE created_at = '01/15/2024'   -- Risky: format may not parse correctly
```

### Explicit Casting

```sql
-- ANSI SQL
CAST(expression AS target_type)

-- MySQL
CAST('123' AS UNSIGNED)
CAST('2024-01-01' AS DATE)
CONVERT(expr, type)

-- PostgreSQL
expression::target_type       -- shorthand
CAST(expression AS INTEGER)

-- Common use: force integer division to return decimal
SELECT CAST(a AS DECIMAL) / b    -- instead of a / b (integer division!)
SELECT a * 1.0 / b               -- alternative trick
```

⚠️ **Integer division trap — the #1 cross-engine silent-bug generator.**
```sql
SELECT 7 / 2        -- MySQL: 3.5000 | PostgreSQL: 3 | SQL Server: 3
SELECT 7 / 2.0      -- All: 3.5
SELECT CAST(7 AS DECIMAL) / 2  -- All: 3.5
```

💡 **Rule of thumb:** the moment you see a `/` in a query that needs to return a fraction (percentages, ratios, averages), **cast one side to `DECIMAL` or multiply by `1.0`**. Don't assume the engine will do the right thing — PostgreSQL and SQL Server silently truncate. The interviewer-favorite bug is `a / b` returning `0` because both are integers and `a < b`.

<div class="quiz" data-quiz-id="q-integer-division">
  <div class="quiz-kind">Guess the output</div>
  <div class="quiz-q">On PostgreSQL, what does <code>SELECT 3 / 4</code> return?</div>
  <ol class="quiz-opts">
    <li><code>0.75</code></li>
    <li data-correct><code>0</code></li>
    <li><code>0.7500</code></li>
    <li>Error</li>
  </ol>
  <div class="quiz-why">Both operands are integers, so Postgres/SQL Server truncate to integer division. Use <code>3 * 1.0 / 4</code> or <code>CAST(3 AS DECIMAL) / 4</code>.</div>
</div>

---

## 0.4 CASE Expressions

```sql
-- Simple CASE
CASE status
    WHEN 'A' THEN 'Active'
    WHEN 'I' THEN 'Inactive'
    ELSE 'Unknown'
END

-- Searched CASE (more flexible)
CASE
    WHEN salary > 100000 THEN 'High'
    WHEN salary > 50000  THEN 'Medium'
    ELSE 'Low'
END
```

⚙️ CASE is an **expression**, not a statement — it returns a value and can appear in SELECT, WHERE, ORDER BY, GROUP BY, and inside aggregate functions.

⚠️ `CASE col WHEN NULL` **never matches** — use `CASE WHEN col IS NULL` instead.

<div class="quiz" data-quiz-id="q-case-null-match">
  <div class="quiz-kind">Guess the output</div>
  <div class="quiz-q">What does this return?</div>
<pre><code class="language-sql">SELECT CASE x
         WHEN NULL THEN 'null!'
         WHEN 1    THEN 'one'
         ELSE 'other'
       END
FROM (VALUES (NULL), (1), (2)) AS t(x);</code></pre>
  <ol class="quiz-opts">
    <li><code>'null!', 'one', 'other'</code></li>
    <li data-correct><code>'other', 'one', 'other'</code></li>
    <li><code>NULL, 'one', 'other'</code></li>
    <li>Error — can't compare to NULL</li>
  </ol>
  <div class="quiz-why">The <strong>simple</strong> <code>CASE x WHEN NULL</code> form expands to <code>x = NULL</code>, which is always UNKNOWN, so it never matches — even when <code>x</code> is actually NULL. The NULL row falls through to <code>ELSE 'other'</code>. Use the <strong>searched</strong> form: <code>CASE WHEN x IS NULL THEN …</code>.</div>
</div>

---

## 0.5 BETWEEN & DISTINCT Nuances

### BETWEEN

```sql
-- BETWEEN is inclusive: includes both endpoints
WHERE id BETWEEN 1 AND 5      -- same as id >= 1 AND id <= 5

-- ⚠️ TIMESTAMP trap:
WHERE created_at BETWEEN '2024-01-01' AND '2024-01-31'
-- MISSES timestamps like '2024-01-31 15:30:00' because
-- '2024-01-31' is interpreted as '2024-01-31 00:00:00'

-- Fix:
WHERE created_at >= '2024-01-01' AND created_at < '2024-02-01'
```

### DISTINCT

```sql
-- DISTINCT applies to the ENTIRE SELECT list
SELECT DISTINCT department, status FROM employees;
-- Deduplicates (department, status) PAIRS — not just department

-- DISTINCT inside aggregate: different behavior
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT department) FROM employees;  -- count of unique departments
SELECT COUNT(department) FROM employees;           -- count of non-NULL values

-- DISTINCT with ORDER BY: ORDER BY columns must appear in SELECT (some engines)
SELECT DISTINCT department FROM employees ORDER BY department;  -- OK
SELECT DISTINCT department FROM employees ORDER BY salary;      -- ERROR in PostgreSQL
```

<div class="quiz" data-quiz-id="q-between-timestamp">
  <div class="quiz-kind">Scenario</div>
  <div class="quiz-q">Your <code>created_at</code> column is <code>TIMESTAMP</code>. You write <code>WHERE created_at BETWEEN '2024-01-01' AND '2024-01-31'</code>. Users report January 31st orders are missing. Why?</div>
  <ol class="quiz-opts">
    <li>BETWEEN is exclusive on the upper bound</li>
    <li data-correct><code>'2024-01-31'</code> is cast to <code>2024-01-31 00:00:00</code>, so any timestamp later that day is excluded</li>
    <li>BETWEEN doesn't work on timestamps</li>
    <li>The dates need single quotes escaped</li>
  </ol>
  <div class="quiz-why">The string date is implicitly cast to midnight. Fix with a half-open range: <code>created_at &gt;= '2024-01-01' AND created_at &lt; '2024-02-01'</code>.</div>
</div>

---

## 0.6 Operator Precedence & Parentheses

⚠️ **`AND` binds tighter than `OR`.** Without parentheses, `WHERE a = 1 OR b = 2 AND c = 3` parses as `WHERE a = 1 OR (b = 2 AND c = 3)` — almost never what was intended.

```sql
-- BUG: reads as "active, OR (premium AND recent)"
WHERE status = 'active' OR plan = 'premium' AND signup_date > '2024-01-01'

-- FIX: parenthesize the OR group
WHERE (status = 'active' OR plan = 'premium') AND signup_date > '2024-01-01'
```

**Precedence (tightest → loosest):** `()` → unary `-`, `NOT` → `*`, `/`, `%` → `+`, `-` → comparison (`=`, `<`, `>`, `LIKE`, `IN`, `BETWEEN`) → `AND` → `OR`.

💡 **Rule of thumb:** whenever you mix `AND` and `OR`, parenthesize explicitly — even when the default grouping is what you want. It makes intent obvious in code review.

<div class="quiz" data-quiz-id="q-precedence-and-or">
  <div class="quiz-kind">Scenario</div>
  <div class="quiz-q">Intent: rows that are either high-priority OR (paid AND recent). Which WHERE clause matches the intent?</div>
  <ol class="quiz-opts">
    <li><code>WHERE priority = 'high' OR paid = 1 AND created_at &gt; '2024-01-01'</code></li>
    <li data-correct>Both A and C give the same result</li>
    <li><code>WHERE priority = 'high' OR (paid = 1 AND created_at &gt; '2024-01-01')</code></li>
    <li><code>WHERE (priority = 'high' OR paid = 1) AND created_at &gt; '2024-01-01'</code></li>
  </ol>
  <div class="quiz-why"><code>AND</code> binds tighter than <code>OR</code>, so A parses exactly as C. D is the wrong grouping — it also requires <code>created_at</code> for the high-priority rows. Always parenthesize to remove ambiguity.</div>
</div>

